[{"caption":"NOM VWAP Bands","indicators":["NOM VWAP Bands"],"authorId":137783,"id":"d47413f1-e618-4a1b-bbcf-0238c09e06b6","text":"This is an enhancement of other VWAP indicators that include standard deviation bands and adds higher timeframes (including fixed monthly and weekly timeframes).","likes":0,"updated":"2020-10-01T22:10:12.955Z","trendingScore":746,"usageScore":21039,"shares":112485,"sources":{"NOMVWAPBands":{"name":"NOMVWAPBands.js"}},"images":["7bc65504-c1b3-42ae-aa72-4afe4f1747b8","98aa54ba-6729-4cbe-b9ac-4546611b9454"],"author":"nom"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"VWAP","entitlement":false,"indicators":["CE VWAP"],"authorId":1881191,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Modified from Tiki VWAP\nCredits to Tiki VWAP","id":"5c33b8a8-9419-4906-8b0d-0619f084f2b6","updated":"2024-01-02T15:59:35.577Z","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"trendingScore":1479,"usageScore":32570,"shares":78009,"sources":{"CEVWAP.js":{"name":"CEVWAP.js"}},"images":[],"author":"CE Codes"},{"caption":"Volume Bulls Bears","authorId":131014,"indicators":["Bulls vs Bears"],"id":"50c636ef-48f2-4995-8a50-65d8c6b87603","text":"An improved volume indicator which attempts to infer the amount of buying and selling pressure within a candle. For a given time slice of an asset, the amount of buying (or bullish) pressure is rendered in green while the amount of selling (or bearish) pressure is rendered in red. The full height of the histogram represents total volume. \n\nBuying and selling pressure is calculated based upon the candle's closing price relative to the full range of the candle (high - low).\n\nA simple moving average of volume is also plotted in yellow.\n\nThis is a collaborative product of the TheoTrade Futures community.","likes":0,"updated":"2020-12-18T04:29:12.867Z","trendingScore":555,"usageScore":13403,"shares":58307,"sources":{"VolumeBullsBears.js":{"name":"VolumeBullsBears.js"}},"images":["af145752-7eeb-4492-b94d-3012f833a7d0","c80e810a-bf66-428b-ad02-5ca3cd997075"],"author":"JackieW"},{"caption":"Tiki Opening Range","authorId":1103,"indicators":["Tiki Opening Range"],"text":"This indicator plots the opening range of a given time period, useful for looking for breakouts from an initial balance area. This indicator may be customizable by the regular start time and duration (e.g. 5, 30, 60 minutes, etc.), and also contains a mid point plot.","id":"5a55a0aa0872330001e20c69","updated":"2019-10-03T20:47:14.625Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":330,"usageScore":10577,"shares":36984,"sources":{"tikiOpeningRange.js":{"name":"tikiOpeningRange.js"}},"images":["49b01d94-93fa-483b-998e-6799f396c915","a59f6786-d37e-4046-aac6-ba5901547f4b"],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"caption":"Tiki Volume","indicators":["Tiki Volume"],"authorId":1103,"id":"5ba3992c70a1997bc7e3a345","text":"This indicator creates a volume histogram that is colored based on the price bars.","updated":"2018-09-24T13:18:14.700Z","likes":0,"shares":28218,"trendingScore":148,"usageScore":4104,"sources":{"tikiVolume.js":{"name":"tikiVolume.js"}},"images":["4d93c85f-4ace-4c6f-8a55-28fbda93015b","97e0eab8-822c-43fa-8faa-b237064a3eb5"],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Fair Value Gao, FVG","entitlement":false,"indicators":["Vinay-FairValueGap"],"authorId":384294,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Like to share this basic script originally created by VINAY in the forum, I have been using it to track FVG , fair value gap in ES and NQ.","id":"3238c33e-11ea-4c87-82a8-3ce1e5f27a2d","updated":"2024-05-18T03:29:36.071Z","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"trendingScore":505,"usageScore":10095,"shares":27037,"sources":{"FVGSbasic.js":{"name":"FVGSbasic.js"}},"images":["fb2a450d-a983-4935-b35d-be52ca836b08"],"author":"KAMELOT"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Delta Footprint by MarketXero","entitlement":false,"indicators":["Delta Footprint by MarketXero"],"authorId":339145,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"The Delta Footprint is heavily inspired by Sierra footprint charts with modifications for legibility. \n\nThe delta volume is shown in the left column (bid-ask) with the text of these bars to the right. The total candle direction for bear/bull is shown in the center with the corresponding color direction. The right side column shows total volume bars and corresponding text for each price level. \n\nThe footprint chart is pushed up half a tick on the y-axis to allow for the price level to align dead center of the corresponding volume bar.\n\nThis script is modified by MarketXero for the Investitrade community from the 'Hector - Footprint' indicator, which was modified from the Sethmo footprint indicator","id":"92250f4c-067e-4378-b67b-867906f954fe","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2026-01-11T00:04:33.212Z","trendingScore":636,"usageScore":5647,"shares":26520,"sources":{"Delta Footprint MarketXero.js":{"name":"Delta Footprint MarketXero.js"}},"images":["a5c1c030-de29-4220-ab0d-4f4ea1b05531","f273a51a-2a96-47ca-9441-e55277f80fe6"],"author":"MarketZero"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Sethmo Price Axis Volume Delta - Offset Bars","entitlement":false,"authorId":130646,"indicators":["Sethmo Price Axis Volume Delta"],"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"This is a fork of the recent \"Price Axis Volume Delta Preview\" indicator.  This indicator ONLY works in the Web version of Tradovate.  The only change is the added ability to offset the bars to the left of the Price axis so you can still read your volume profile.","id":"b17312b9-1a24-4888-a8c2-b717ada25144","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2022-02-28T03:14:55.797Z","trendingScore":368,"usageScore":3179,"shares":24767,"sources":{"sethmoPriceAxisDelta.js":{"name":"sethmoPriceAxisDelta.js"}},"images":["6b99ce54-8e07-4770-8e03-52fce2d0c4b6"],"author":"Seth Mo"},{"caption":"Delta Divergence","indicators":["Delta Divergence"],"authorId":87472,"text":"Delta gives us a broad sense for each bar of whether we have more aggressive buying or selling. \n\nWe can compare Delta between bars to get a sense of whether supply and demand are rising or falling, Delta Divergence tells us when the delta across price bars is not moving in the same direction as price.\n\nExample:\n1. Bearish Divergence ==> Price has made a new high but there was more selling than buying.\n2. Bullish Divergence ==> Price has made a new low but there was more buying than selling.\n\nPlots\nRed dot above the high when price makes higher high on negative delta\nGreen dot below the low when price makes lower low on positive delta","id":"84c984c9-53be-460c-846f-017a1538270b","likes":0,"updated":"2020-08-23T01:46:49.134Z","shares":23955,"trendingScore":72,"usageScore":2102,"sources":{"deltaDivergence":{"name":"deltaDivergence.js"}},"images":["29026f6f-1a79-4118-a252-87252d8bf4db","4a255fd5-efc6-40cf-b257-c6f52e2ef91a"],"author":"Sanjay Dubey"},{"caption":"p2f - Dead Simple Reversal","indicators":["p2f - Dead Simple Reversal"],"authorId":138571,"text":"An indicator for detecting potential reversal points by measuring for 'extreme' lows or highs. Useful for reversion trading strategies.","id":"c139ae93-4681-46c3-b1a1-ecb1da48a802","updated":"2020-09-27T00:45:22.891Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":168,"usageScore":4462,"shares":22619,"sources":{"p2fDeadSimpleReversal":{"name":"p2fDeadSimpleReversal.js"}},"images":["37f4af19-18af-4bdb-ad66-0fbf0b48bd38","c06a30c8-42d4-4950-b23d-511b388318f3"],"author":"paidtofade"},{"caption":"Delta Histogram","indicators":["Delta Histogram"],"authorId":87472,"id":"5d8502dffeb3aec7a77d719b","text":"This indicator creates a delta histogram that is colored based on delta value for each bars.","updated":"2019-09-20T16:49:32.114Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":140,"usageScore":3085,"shares":21134,"sources":{"deltaHistogram":{"name":"deltaHistogram.js"}},"images":["d8dcbea7-b908-4590-a863-cb0da7979974","dbf09f4d-04dd-44ab-9deb-a879916c1d9c"],"author":"Sanjay Dubey"},{"caption":"ATR TrailStop w/Fib Target Prices","authorId":140606,"indicators":["ATR TrailStop w/Fib Targets"],"id":"28c84270-f84f-4ab7-a310-4259b1b14885","text":"This study is a port of the ATR TrailStop study from TOS.  It identifies trends and provides a trailing stop for you.  This study also uses fib levels to incorporate support and resistance levels and to provide price targets on the chart.","updated":"2020-09-04T03:20:44.392Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":128,"usageScore":2184,"shares":20803,"sources":{"atrTrailStop_wTargets":{"name":"atrTrailStop_wTargets.js"}},"images":["92bba657-9c59-478a-b44c-3900d92e416f","e200ff95-0a9f-4f48-84cc-a72203cde348"],"author":"Scott K"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Sethmo Large Delta Bubbles","entitlement":false,"authorId":130646,"indicators":["Sethmo Large Delta Bubbles"],"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"d097dca9-8e99-4bd3-a540-082b16865f4e","text":"Plots bubbles on the chart where delta is greater than the set threshold. Bubble size increases with delta size.","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2022-03-08T15:56:28.220Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":703,"usageScore":8075,"shares":20772,"sources":{"sethmoLargeVolumeTrades.js":{"name":"sethmoLargeVolumeTrades.js"}},"images":["c8150212-8762-4be1-a55b-bf5209b81269"],"author":"Seth Mo"},{"caption":"Tiki VWAP","authorId":1103,"indicators":["Tiki VWAP"],"text":"This indicator improves on Tradovate's native VWAP indicator by providing standard deviation bands and an ability to plot the bid and ask volumes.","id":"5ab936603f3f220001f27fd2","likes":0,"updated":"2020-04-17T16:04:33.173Z","shares":20393,"trendingScore":91,"usageScore":3590,"sources":{"tikiVWAP.js":{"name":"tikiVWAP.js"}},"images":["c416ef56-ce77-4825-a31c-88d06da754df","fddbe7ac-6f3e-41dd-9f66-40219a3cf49f"],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"caption":"Tiki Cumulative Delta Line","authorId":1103,"indicators":["Tiki Cumulative Delta Line"],"text":"This improves the native Cumulative Delta indicator by adding a zero line and a session time reset capability.  This version is also plotted as a line instead of candlesticks.","id":"5dd2ca290a0651522bc1c96a","updated":"2019-11-18T16:43:21.036Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":90,"usageScore":1517,"shares":20010,"sources":{"tikiCumulativeDeltaLine.js":{"name":"tikiCumulativeDeltaLine.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"caption":"Tiki OHLC","indicators":["Tiki OHLC"],"authorId":1103,"text":"This indicator will plot the previous session Open/High/Low/Close and track the current session's Open, High and Low, expanding the range as you trade.  Great in combination with Tiki Opening Range for establishing key ranges for the day.","id":"5ac100c84c1e000001feba18","updated":"2020-01-16T01:47:26.745Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":127,"usageScore":3053,"shares":19955,"sources":{"tikiOHLC.js":{"name":"tikiOHLC.js"}},"images":["a303da9e-27eb-40dc-b130-c367185dabff","acbdd7c1-c5ef-4d0d-a3be-065e0960d23f"],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"caption":"Tiki Squeeze","indicators":["Tiki Squeeze"],"authorId":1103,"text":"The Squeeze indicator attempts to identify periods of consolidation in a market. In general the market is either in a period of quiet consolidation or vertical price discovery. Once a market enters into a “squeeze”, we watch the overall market momentum to help forecast the market direction and await a release of market energy.\n\nThe red and green dots along the zero line indicate if there is a squeeze. A red dot means there is a squeeze condition in effect. A green dot means that we are not currently in a squeeze. The first green dot after one or more red dots is where the squeeze is said to have “fired”. The red and blue histogram indicates momentum. If above zero momentum is increasing, the histogram will by light blue. If above zero momentum is decreasing, it will be dark blue. Inversely, the histogram will paint yellow or red to portray increasing or decreasing momentum below the zero line.","id":"5bef2c78cd8bd8d9699811ec","updated":"2018-11-16T20:45:44.433Z","likes":0,"shares":19206,"trendingScore":50,"usageScore":2104,"sources":{"tikiSqueeze.js":{"name":"tikiSqueeze.js"}},"images":["031ff58e-5131-4516-bf1e-39d5f5efbe57","7f2c2ea2-382b-4f4d-8e1c-2c1e46d2cf37"],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"caption":"p2f - Kaufman Adaptive Moving Average","authorId":138571,"indicators":["p2f - Adaptive Moving Average"],"id":"ba1929d2-b4ac-4985-9e9b-52e2b4602701","text":"This study calculates and displays an Adaptive Moving Average of the data. This moving average was developed by Perry Kaufman. It is also sometimes referred to using the acronym KAMA.","likes":0,"updated":"2020-07-04T22:09:57.876Z","shares":18912,"trendingScore":17,"usageScore":1009,"sources":{"p2f-kama":{"name":"p2f-kama.js"}},"images":["5930b7f2-b32a-4118-bda6-3e4852187ed7","850dde62-e65d-4cb0-889c-f75e56fd466b"],"author":"paidtofade"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Volume Delta Grid","indicators":["Volume Delta Grid"],"authorId":204597,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Displays a text grid containing entries for bid/ask volumes and deltas on a per bar basis and cumulatively for today.","id":"d38003f9-4f72-4910-b442-a858a99b6fc6","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2021-09-16T17:26:26.880Z","shares":18693,"trendingScore":129,"usageScore":1928,"sources":{"VolumeDeltaGrid.js":{"name":"VolumeDeltaGrid.js"}},"images":["395ab70c-af75-4339-9fda-9290e6c0b11e","9035f22a-4ba9-4c31-9aac-69059af4e421"],"author":"rossketeer"},{"caption":"p2f - Anchored VWAP","indicators":["p2f - Anchored VWAP"],"authorId":138571,"id":"ec7dadf7-449a-4e18-b3af-835a068df57e","text":"The anchored VWAP is a volume weighted moving average starting at a chosen 'anchor' date and time. Includes configurable deviation bands.","updated":"2021-01-06T01:31:29.620Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":163,"usageScore":4178,"shares":16929,"sources":{"p2f-aVWAP":{"name":"p2f-aVWAP.js"}},"images":[],"author":"paidtofade"},{"caption":"Pivot Points with 3 levels","authorId":16592,"indicators":["Daily PPoints"],"text":"Pivot Points including PP, S1, S2, S3, R1, R2, R3 and the middle lines. ","id":"5e27318396f71211e47d10f8","likes":0,"updated":"2021-01-13T19:12:35.862Z","trendingScore":112,"usageScore":2105,"shares":16535,"sources":{"PPoints_3_Levels":{"name":"PPoints_3_Levels.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Bas"},{"caption":"SuperTrend","indicators":["SuperTrend"],"authorId":28582,"text":"Some improvements on the Tiki Supertrend with coloring, and with tick rounding.  The multiplier is rounded to the nearest 0.25 now as well. ","id":"5c4b3cd2b82e441c035e535e","updated":"2019-01-27T14:33:52.484Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":101,"usageScore":1282,"shares":16364,"sources":{"superTrend":{"name":"superTrend.js"}},"images":[],"author":"mortdiggiddy"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"template","module":"funCharts","caption":"Market Profile/Volume Profile - Regular and After Hours Split","indicators":[],"authorId":62939,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"5a06678c-4947-4c98-b54f-033cd1b8890b","text":"A template that attempts to capture all elements of market and volume profile in the most visual way possible. The first two 30 minute ranges (A and B period) are highlighted green to represent the \"Initial Balance.\" Period O represents the traditional settlement period prior to October 26, 2020 and is highlighted white to quickly identify the close area of the day.","updated":"2021-05-06T02:40:59.304Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":84,"shares":16210,"sources":{"Market Profile/Volume Profile - Regular and After Hours Split":{"name":"Market Profile/Volume Profile - Regular and After Hours Split.template.tradovate"}},"images":["5f966f51-bad5-4be2-8a20-dc7f7c8d672e","8e09b345-ff94-420d-8c0c-59434e6c3859","b9419da2-5151-4bef-894b-604a7732929e"],"author":"Machinator"},{"caption":"Day Trading Academy MACD BB's","indicators":["MACD BBs"],"authorId":28593,"text":"Day Trading Academy MACD BB's","id":"5bacad7dd67bd18571d8d933","updated":"2018-09-27T10:21:35.612Z","likes":0,"shares":15404,"trendingScore":12,"usageScore":190,"sources":{"dtaMacdBBs":{"name":"dtaMacdBBs.js"}},"images":["79ec4c20-7550-4292-bee2-ff8e093cd72b","ff0f1122-856e-4e2e-b35d-dda5c2367a2d"],"author":"SpeedUpTrader"},{"caption":"The VPOC of each bar (the price with the highest volume)","indicators":["VPOC (BAR)"],"authorId":87472,"id":"dc42694a-4401-488b-b606-965e14f37340","text":"Volume point of control(VPOC), refers to the price at which the highest volume of trading occurred. This indicator will calculate VPOC in real time and plot rectangle box around VPOC for each candlestick/bar.  Works only on Bid-Ask Volume chart type.","updated":"2020-09-02T01:54:35.321Z","likes":0,"shares":15009,"trendingScore":106,"usageScore":2389,"sources":{"barVPOC":{"name":"barVPOC.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Sanjay Dubey"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"https://community.tradovate.com/t/new-sessions-overlay/8676/5","caption":"SuperSessions","entitlement":false,"indicators":["SuperSessions"],"authorId":753811,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Easily track daily high volume trading times. Displays up to three customizable sessions simultaneously.","id":"4a4c36a2-8c0a-4b71-8eaa-f9b929dc757f","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2024-04-08T07:15:46.970Z","trendingScore":184,"usageScore":3539,"shares":14607,"sources":{"SuperSessions.js":{"name":"SuperSessions.js"}},"images":["30cd3109-89dd-447f-8c1a-ab02a53fa8bb","ac9fe280-d2f9-49b7-a6c8-76c1428d555f","e1b4521b-1858-45a4-a2af-96abc0005a40"],"author":"ekb"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"template","module":"funCharts","caption":"Better Delta Footprint 15min","indicators":[],"authorId":130646,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"a08d0e28-f800-4609-bc3e-1084350b2775","text":"Used indicators: LDT - Remaining Time and Ticks, Sethmo Settlement, Sethmo Delta Histogram, LDT - Stacked Imbalances (for New Charts), Sethmo Volume Delta Grid Clean, Sethmo Better Delta Flow, Volume Profiles, Sethmo Price Axis Volume Delta, VWAP","updated":"2022-02-28T02:48:27.529Z","likes":0,"shares":14598,"trendingScore":78,"sources":{"Better Delta Footprint 15min":{"name":"Better Delta Footprint 15min.template.tradovate"}},"images":["beda63f3-7188-48e7-84cc-bcaabaeba5cf"],"author":"Seth Mo"},{"caption":"Cumulative Delta Histogram","authorId":87472,"indicators":["Cumulative Delta Histogram"],"id":"09611e15-298f-4317-a13b-e7c79c6b9aff","text":"Delta refers to the net difference between buying and selling volume at each price level. Cumulative Delta builds upon this concept by recording a cumulative tally of these differences in buying vs selling volume. Plotted as histogram auto colored based on cumulative delta values, you can reset at specified session time + feature to enable line drawing on top of histogram.","updated":"2020-09-15T20:13:54.070Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":58,"usageScore":662,"shares":13501,"sources":{"cumulativeDeltaHistogram":{"name":"cumulativeDeltaHistogram.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Sanjay Dubey"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Latter-day Trader: Time and Ticks Countdown","authorId":207522,"indicators":["LDT - Remaining Time and Ticks"],"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Shows the remaining time for MINUTE charts or remaining TICKS. Does not correctly seconds chart, range, momentum, renko, etc. Also, this only works with NEW charts, not Legacy charts.\n\nThere is a known bug where the remaining time is wrong when you change the time frame of t he current chart (i.e. 1 minute to 5 minutes). To fix this, you will have to navigate to a new tab or refresh the chart/platform. Or you can try going into the settings and click Save. This is just a quirk with the Tradovate platform.\n\nAnd as always, if this indicator or any of my other ones have helped you profit, please consider sending a tip my way. Visit buymeacoffee.com/latterdaytrader and send me a drink.","id":"954df5a0-79cb-49c5-a342-7a16f6ce431f","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"20