e":"workspace","caption":"1 tpo per plot","indicators":[],"authorId":2126,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"78b7e5f8-766b-44ac-a4bf-ae64e8565aa6","text":"This is a workspace that uses a modified version of the TPO chart. It plots a new tpo volume profile for each 30 minute period. The letters have been shaded out to better show the open and close arrows. Tpo counts would just be a measure of how many ticks range (if set to 1 per box)  for that period. Below this chart is a separate 30 minute bid/ask chart with the new volume delta grid. This works around some of the issues using certain tools on the tpo charts.  You may have to scunch up the price of the bottom chart to fully display the volume grid.  You will have to keep an eye out and make sure the  two charts are lined up.","updated":"2021-05-14T02:22:32.211Z","likes":0,"shares":8707,"trendingScore":59,"sources":{"1 tpo per plot":{"name":"1 tpo per plot.workspace.tradovate"}},"images":["2503afac-9116-4907-a579-395e003970f8"],"author":"JoshuaW"},{"caption":"Tiki SuperTrend","authorId":1103,"indicators":["Tiki SuperTrend"],"text":"Aloha from Tiki Dave!\n\nThe SuperTrend indicator was requested by Robert in the forums, and I gave it a shot.  Currently Tradovate doesn't support coloring of the plot lines, but it seems to work really well otherwise!  ","id":"59de8773267ea700016eba4f","updated":"2018-09-24T13:17:58.977Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":17,"usageScore":920,"shares":8353,"sources":{"tikiSuperTrend.js":{"name":"tikiSuperTrend.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"https://community.tradovate.com/t/overnight-high-low-onh-onl-indicator/6972","caption":"Eman Overnight High Low (ONHL)","entitlement":false,"indicators":["Eman Overnight High Low (ONHL)"],"authorId":574029,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"This tool tracks the overnight or ETH session high and low range (ONH for the high, ONL for the low). During RTH these levels are maintained. Once RTH ends they reset and begin tracking once again. Labels are automatically included, and the level values may be enabled or disabled.","id":"bfeb8350-dc9b-40c2-849f-28a70a452919","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2023-03-21T14:45:37.556Z","trendingScore":100,"usageScore":2198,"shares":7789,"sources":{"emanONHL.js":{"name":"emanONHL.js"}},"images":["798f7975-077e-46db-81e5-4ea4f0c3bbca","dc0303ad-51bc-40aa-b7e6-26f8f84e62a4"],"author":"emansenpai"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Position Drawing Tool","entitlement":false,"authorId":285399,"indicators":["Long/Short Position"],"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Long/Short Position Drawing Tool. The Take Profit point is determined by the Risk Reward Ratio that you enter - default 3.14. You can change its appearance or parameters by creating a drawing, double clicking on it to open the details panel. You can save a default state for the drawing as well by checking Save As Default.","id":"6ca60f3c-77a1-466a-9ed6-2cee77d24666","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2022-01-28T21:00:13.010Z","likes":0,"shares":7698,"trendingScore":68,"sources":{"positionTool.js":{"name":"positionTool.js"}},"images":["575976ea-01d8-4a33-915f-227c7a4ec775"],"author":"alennert"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"https://community.tradovate.com/t/ichimoku-with-future-cloud/5172","caption":"Ichimoku (with future cloud)","entitlement":false,"authorId":139990,"indicators":["Ichimoku"],"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"This is an Ichimoku indicator with the cloud projected into the future (missing in another version found on here). It uses shifts to move the lagging span and cloud. I also handled the cloud fill differently, just with more line plots, for simplicity.","id":"77eb4647-837a-4382-ad48-12cc984a365c","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2022-07-28T22:56:00.691Z","likes":0,"shares":7271,"trendingScore":80,"usageScore":1959,"sources":{"Ichimoku.js":{"name":"Ichimoku.js"}},"images":["64d11f79-71d2-42a9-b4d4-a8cf7bda574f"],"author":"Brian"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Williams Alligator","indicators":["Williams Alligator"],"authorId":186417,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"6170182e-f1ed-40d5-bb2c-0ee38fee7540","text":"This is the Williams Alligator the way Bill Williams designed it. Three smoothed moving averages comprise the Jaws (blue), Teeth (red), and Lips (green). Williams' settings are the default settings.","updated":"2021-09-23T19:39:24.904Z","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"shares":7232,"trendingScore":16,"usageScore":703,"sources":{"Williams_Alligator.js":{"name":"Williams_Alligator.js"}},"images":["d85ff2d8-9ab5-4cd0-8d59-6668f509cb30"],"author":"Otto Blink"},{"caption":"EMA Ribbon","indicators":["EMA Ribbon"],"authorId":28582,"text":"Ribbon that changes colors based on a fast, slow, and signal EMA.\n\nConditions:\n\nWhen fast > slow and signal > fast: Ribbon fill is light green\nWhen fast > slow and signal <= fast: Ribbon fill is bright green\nWhen fast <= slow and signal < fast: Ribbon is light red\nWhen fast <= slow and signal >= fast: Ribbon is bright red\n\nThe fast and slow EMA also change colors:\n\nWhen fast > slow: fast is bright green and slow is cyan\nWhen fast <= slow: fast is bright red and slow is magenta\n\nThe fast and slow EMA can be rounded to the nearest tick. The default rounding is 1, if set to 0 then there is no rounding.\n\nEnjoy.","id":"5c05a6fd1575fd4b7bb84aa9","updated":"2018-12-08T22:42:02.505Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":34,"usageScore":794,"shares":7177,"sources":{"movingAverageRibbon":{"name":"movingAverageRibbon.js"}},"images":[],"author":"mortdiggiddy"},{"caption":"MACD","authorId":16592,"indicators":["MACD"],"id":"c40ee448-9599-4c5d-a312-68121fedb68f","text":"The original MACD","updated":"2020-08-27T16:30:46.275Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":33,"usageScore":208,"shares":7089,"sources":{"MACD_2.js":{"name":"MACD_2.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Bas"},{"caption":"Combined Session Levels with IB and ORB","text":"This program calculates and visualizes key session high and low levels for different market sessions, helping traders identify critical price zones throughout the trading day. It includes the Asian, London, Pre-market, and New York sessions, along with the initial balance and midpoint for the NYC opening range.\n\nSession Timeframes (EST) & Label Adjustments:\nAsian Session: 6:00 PM – 4:00 AM (Label: 6:00 PM – 3:30 AM due to London overlap)\nLondon Session: 4:00 AM – 8:30 AM (Label: 3:30 AM – 8:30 AM due to possible economic data impact)\nPre-market Session: 8:30 AM – 9:30 AM (Potential economic data effect)\nNew York Initial Balance (Market Open): 9:30 AM – 10:30 AM (Use IB for directional bias. Previous IB levels act as support & resistance or value area breakout targets toward the top of balance.)\nNYC Opening Range: 9:30 AM – 9:45 AM (According to Edgeful data, 80% of the time, only one side of the range breaks first. Trade the second break, not the first, for an edgeful statistical advantage.)\nsorry for overlap","updated":"2025-02-15T14:53:39.192Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"b07026a1-8593-40f2-b1de-6f9a9c7a0926","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["Session High and Low for Asia, London, Pre-market Data, Initial Balance, and NYC Opening Range. Additionally, it calculates the new initial balance and midpoint for the NYC opening range session."],"authorId":2219171,"likes":0,"shares":6907,"trendingScore":157,"usageScore":1963,"sources":{"SESSIONSNYCIB.js":{"name":"SESSIONSNYCIB.js"}},"images":[],"author":"servantthought"},{"caption":"Fair Value Gap","text":"This is a better FVG indicator, it can handle mitigation bettre","updated":"2025-01-27T06:36:31.198Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"85e2a7c6-47a6-4914-808f-023fd4f5bacb","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["FVG-Rects"],"authorId":1767676,"likes":0,"trendingScore":70,"usageScore":1648,"shares":6907,"sources":{"FVG_Rects.js":{"name":"FVG_Rects.js"}},"images":[],"author":"VINAYPAL VEMULA"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Fibonacci Pivot Points v2","indicators":["Fibonacci Pivot Points v2"],"authorId":187183,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"0b0f631b-7e57-4de5-a948-31453aa2be6c","text":"Install \"Fibonacci Pivot Points v1\" if you want standard indicator values.\nVersion 2 is unorthodox.\n\nThis version of Fibonacci Pivot Points places three times greater weight on previous day closing price than the standard Fibonacci Pivot Points. The influence came from how Woodie's Pivot Point is calculated. Think of \"exponential moving average vs. simple moving average\".","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2021-06-14T14:46:00.080Z","shares":6746,"trendingScore":65,"usageScore":843,"sources":{"bnotb_Fibonacci_Pivots_v2.js":{"name":"bnotb_Fibonacci_Pivots_v2.js"}},"images":[],"author":"bnotb"},{"caption":"Moving Average WonderCloud","authorId":140606,"indicators":["Moving Avg WonderCloud"],"text":"Draws and colors a  cloud based on the fast and slow input periods.  Can select SMA, EMA, HULL, Weighted for moving averages.","id":"89f2865a-a0b2-4e58-9bdc-b7a222fb12cd","likes":0,"updated":"2020-07-30T06:36:23.701Z","shares":6669,"trendingScore":18,"usageScore":838,"sources":{"movAvg_WonderCloud":{"name":"movAvg_WonderCloud.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Scott K"},{"caption":"Camarilla Pivot Points","indicators":["CamarillaPivotPoints"],"authorId":28582,"text":"Camarilla Pivots, including level 5s.","id":"5c05af391189cd094749f63f","updated":"2018-12-11T14:12:16.531Z","likes":0,"shares":6479,"trendingScore":27,"usageScore":929,"sources":{"camarillaPivotPoints":{"name":"camarillaPivotPoints.js"}},"images":[],"author":"mortdiggiddy"},{"caption":"Pivot Points with middle","indicators":["PivotPoints Daily"],"authorId":31356,"id":"5bd2d274880b292992c53a59","text":"Daily Pivot Points with middle value