Candlestick Reversal System","entitlement":false,"indicators":["Candlestick Reversals"],"authorId":226906,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"In the book - Secrets of a Pivot Boss: Revealing Proven Methods for Profiting in the Market by Franklin Ochoa, four different types of reversal systems using candlestick patterns were introduced. This indicator is inspired by the book and the trading view \"Candlestick-Reversal-System\" contribution. \n\nFollowing Reversal Systems are in the indicator:\n- Extreme Reversal\n- Outside Reversal\n- Doji Reversal\n- Wick Reversal\n\nPlease read the book for more information on the reversal systems themselves.","id":"569fed8c-9b7a-4471-b107-054afb920ffd","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2023-08-19T20:30:20.286Z","trendingScore":40,"usageScore":595,"shares":5936,"sources":{"Reversal.js":{"name":"Reversal.js"}},"images":["289a1817-90ad-4ea4-9560-ed742fc55674","3eadd5de-de8d-4d1c-b2c9-56cb1d58b89d"],"author":"CaliTrader"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Tiki VWAPOC","entitlement":false,"indicators":["Tiki VWAPOC"],"authorId":1103,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Provides a developing VPOC plot on the Tiki VWAP indicator.","id":"26939774-99e6-45b6-821e-9f826f3fd020","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2024-11-12T20:12:00.480Z","shares":5915,"trendingScore":40,"usageScore":1110,"sources":{"tikiVWAPOC.js":{"name":"tikiVWAPOC.js"}},"images":["9a322d8e-e2e1-4105-aa81-4c4062c71adc"],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"caption":"NukeTIMER - Candle Countdown","text":"NukeTIMER is a lightweight, real-time indicator that displays a countdown timer directly on your chart, showing the remaining time for the current candle to close. Designed for Tradovate users, it helps traders precisely time entries and exits, monitor intraday price action, and make faster decisions without constantly glancing at the clock. Perfect for scalpers, day traders, and anyone who needs accurate candle timing at a glance.","updated":"2025-09-24T17:59:44.200Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"5af525f2-0b7e-473e-a9ad-b1f6f45a72a4","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["NukeGuy - Candle Countdown Timer"],"authorId":4288627,"likes":0,"shares":5912,"trendingScore":478,"usageScore":6338,"sources":{"NukeTIMER.js":{"name":"NukeTIMER.js"}},"images":["1ca7f56a-8847-46f3-8127-b3f9b5396908"],"author":"NukeGuy"},{"caption":"Volume Footprint UU","text":"The Ultimate Volume Footprint Chart\n\nBuy/Sell\nDelta Footprint\nImbalances\nPOC\nVA\nAnd more","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"458a663a-5cbe-430b-b83b-c33dc39830ee","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["~~~VFUU~~~"],"authorId":5094514,"likes":0,"updated":"2026-05-12T10:53:07.233Z","trendingScore":285,"usageScore":1267,"shares":5784,"sources":{"VFU_U.js":{"name":"VFU_U.js"}},"images":["47d911cf-cbc0-47fc-a4c0-6261da8316ae","6d99d6eb-c192-450d-8090-1f6c69747a2a","db795964-ce05-4c84-9c28-bc2e04dcb129"],"author":"Unlimitidities"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Sethmo Basic BidAsk Footprint Variable Resolution","entitlement":false,"authorId":130646,"indicators":["Sethmo Better Bid Ask Footprint"],"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"A basic BidAsk Footprint with Vpoc per bar and variable resolution. You will need to black out the candles as this indicator overlays on top of the chart.\n\nI also published a Basic BidAsk Footprint template that includes stacked imbalances, VP, delta histogram, and volume delta grid","id":"2ec3f012-71ef-4c3a-bcca-8941eafb3396","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2022-03-01T14:35:30.423Z","likes":0,"usageScore":28,"shares":5749,"trendingScore":13,"sources":{"sethmobidAskFootprint":{"name":"sethmobidAskFootprint"}},"images":["59cca1ec-e2d3-4331-ad49-aa7abf957885","bcbf319c-aa96-4095-8fc3-d201e7902441"],"author":"Seth Mo"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Latter-day Trader: Stochastic RSI","indicators":["LDT - Stochastic RSI"],"authorId":207522,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Calculates the RSI and uses that as the input for the Stochastic formula. Supports multiple moving average and price types. Also includes a mid-line, overbought line, and oversold lines. The last two are configurable.","id":"4b07370c-ba6b-4f0d-90ed-d0e2ad33ee9d","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2021-04-26T23:54:50.307Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":24,"shares":5652,"usageScore":781,"sources":{"HMA.js":{"name":"HMA.js"},"LDT_Stochastic_RSI.js":{"name":"LDT_Stochastic_RSI.js"}},"images":[],"author":"LatterDayTrader"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"template","module":"funCharts","caption":"order flow 2024","indicators":[],"authorId":2114368,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Used indicators: Volume Profiles, Tiki VWAPOC, Bulls vs Bears","id":"a72a2b3f-8df6-4fe6-ab9a-303a5c829eb0","updated":"2024-01-23T17:04:24.618Z","likes":0,"shares":5460,"trendingScore":42,"sources":{"order flow 2024":{"name":"order flow 2024.template.tradovate"}},"images":[],"author":"juju"},{"caption":"Tiki Elder Impulse","indicators":["Tiki Elder Impulse"],"authorId":1103,"id":"5ba01fdfd67bd1943cd8d550","text":"Dr. Alexander Elder is the author of two bestselling trading books, Trading for a Living and Come into my Trading Room. He is also known for many trading tactics including the Triple Screen Trading and the Impulse System.  This system combines a relatively short EMA with the standard MACD to find market momentum. When the two indicators align, they show an impulse move.","updated":"2018-09-24T13:17:22.286Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":6,"shares":5392,"usageScore":288,"sources":{"tikiElderImpulse.js":{"name":"tikiElderImpulse.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Previous OHLC","entitlement":false,"authorId":286145,"indicators":["Previous OHLC"],"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"efc40f81-27b8-4b45-ac88-95de374c5541","text":"Previous OHLC","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2021-11-26T12:21:01.515Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":54,"usageScore":1330,"shares":5344,"sources":{"Previous OHLC_PreviousOHLC.js":{"name":"Previous OHLC_PreviousOHLC.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Max"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"https://community.tradovate.com/t/price-action-session-candlestick-bar-counter-5min/5237","caption":"Price Action Session Candlestick Bar Counter 5min","entitlement":false,"authorId":131014,"indicators":["Bar Counter 5min"],"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"116f5a96-a7bc-4445-8462-cd4118086cb5","text":"An Al Brooks style 5min bar count labeler. This custom indicator will label bar 1 and every even bar in the regular trading cash session on a 5min candlestick chart.","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2023-03-16T11:48:20.405Z","shares":5321,"trendingScore":80,"usageScore":2143,"sources":{"barCounter5min.js":{"name":"barCounter5min.js"}},"images":["1971427a-8215-430e-ac61-f9c59a8504bb","d9641c71-1fa1-4f08-bec4-bdaf252cc1a9"],"author":"JackieW"},{"caption":"Fair Value Gap (FVG)","text":"This indicator identifies and plots Fair Value Gaps on the chart.\n\nFVGs are inefficiencies or imbalances in the market that occur when there is a significant price movement, leaving a gap between the wicks of three consecutive bars.\n\nThese gaps often act as magnets for price, suggesting potential areas of support or resistance.\n\nFeatures:\n- Automatically detects and draws both Bullish and Bearish FVGs.\n- Extends the FVG boxes until they are \"filled\" or \"mitigated\" by price action.\n- Draws a dashed line at the 50% midpoint of the FVG, a key level for traders.\n- Customizable colors for bullish and bearish gaps.\n- Adjustable line opacity, FVG count, and minimum gap size.\n- Robust error handling and performance optimization.","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"9675b73d-7c51-4ad3-a584-70a05e3fdb55","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["Fair Value Gaps"],"authorId":155358,"likes":0,"updated":"2025-06-30T02:08:19.353Z","trendingScore":115,"usageScore":1524,"shares":5291,"sources":{"fvg.js":{"name":"fvg.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Vamp"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Sethmo Initial Balance with Custom Extensions","entitlement":false,"indicators":["Sethmo Initial Balance Custom Extensions"],"authorId":130646,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"c9e6c5a6-b503-4f55-a1a7-650a86686149","text":"Simple Initial balance indicator with two customizable extensions.  I like the +/-50 and 100% extensions, or if things are getting spicy, the +/-150% extension.  Includes labels for each line.","updated":"2022-02-05T16:53:10.898Z","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"trendingScore":44,"usageScore":1515,"shares":5216,"sources":{"sethmoIB.js":{"name":"sethmoIB.js"}},"images":["c6d10ff7-8405-466b-81f7-1945413e4c22"],"author":"Seth Mo"},{"caption":"p2f - Overlay Range Boxes (ORBs)","indicators":["p2f - Overlay Range Boxes"],"authorId":138571,"id":"6ff0c3cc-efca-4b54-a012-4ac863737382","text":"Incorporate longer time frames without taking your eyes off of the smaller time frame, by using higher time frame range boxes overlayed on top of the current time frame. Use higher order levels for entry and exit.","likes":0,"entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2021-03-03T03:10:17.451Z","shares":5183,"trendingScore":30,"usageScore":712,"sources":{"p2fRangeBoxes.js":{"name":"p2fRangeBoxes.js"}},"images":[],"author":"paidtofade"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","caption":"Opening Range (30 seconds)","indicators":["Seconds Opening Range"],"authorId":16592,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"This is the Tiki Opening Range indicator with the option to select 30 second range periods.","id":"e720ef48-d9ff-42d8-91fe-4bdf55de9031","updated":"2021-02-22T14:01:33.465Z","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"shares":5144,"trendingScore":18,"usageScore":877,"sources":{"SecondsOpeningRange.js":{"name":"SecondsOpeningRange.js"}},"images":["6d8278ec-1c65-4884-948a-95d028c22ec9"],"author":"Bas"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Sethmo Golden Fibonacci Retracement Tool","entitlement":false,"authorId":130646,"indicators":["+ Golden Fibonacci Retracement"],"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"This is a fork of the \"Improved Fibonacci Retracement\" tool created by Alennert.\n\nBy default, the Fibonacci levels are setup to highlight the golden ratio zones at 0.618-0.65 and 1.618-1.65.\n\nYou can modify any of the levels or the zone opacity for each fill zone.\n(Note: If the zone opacity is set to > 0, clicking and dragging on the zone will also move the fib lines.  If the zone opacity is set to 0, it acts like the original fib tool)\n\nYou can also choose whether you want the zone labels to appear on the left or right side of the Fibonacci levels.","id":"b2b92a6d-9b3b-4bba-ad89-6c4ce9cfc18a","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2021-12-11T21:29:08.160Z","trendingScore":38,"shares":5045,"sources":{"sethmoFibRetracement.js":{"name":"sethmoFibRetracement.js"}},"images":["3fcfb6a9-7dcb-4521-8660-b8934e055a9e","baa1646c-b610-43a9-aa2b-d9b9160e2e22"],"author":"Seth Mo"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Delta Divergence Signals (w/ Absorbtion Labels)","entitlement":false,"indicators":["Delta Divergence Signals"],"authorId":553965,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"These are divergence signals for per candle delta. If a candle closes up but has negative delta, it will show a bearish divergence signal above the candle, and vice versa for short divergence signals. There is a filter option to only show divergence signals if the delta exceeds your set threshold. There are labels that can be toggled on/off that show the delta (how many contracts were absorbed when price moved in the opposite direction).","id":"7e77ffe1-28be-40d3-8d99-7cf9b449720a","updated":"2024-08-31T21:57:23.054Z","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"trendingScore":117,"usageScore":1779,"shares":5036,"sources":{"DeltaDivergenceSignals.js":{"name":"DeltaDivergenceSignals.js"}},"images":["0fe77e8d-fa0f-4ae3-aa7f-072916c64f82"],"author":"tommytrades"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Latter-day Trader: Stacked Imbalances (for New Charts)","indicators":["LDT - Stacked Imbalances (for New Charts)"],"authorId":207522,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Same core logic as the original Stacked Imbalances indicator, but changed the plotter to work with New Charts.\n\nIf you find this or any of my other indicators useful to your trading, please consider tipping me at buymeacoffee.com/latterdaytrader","id":"a277ab7f-fc47-4e9a-b03e-0243e3c31ae3","updated":"2021-07-07T21:34:23.702Z","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"shares":4972,"trendingScore":19,"usageScore":575,"sources":{"LDT_Stacked_Imbalances.js":{"name":"LDT_Stacked_Imbalances.js"}},"images":[],"author":"LatterDayTrader"},{"caption":"OGC Don't Diddle","authorId":86160,"indicators":["OGC Hull No Diddle"],"text":"As the @RealBrianWatt says - \"Don't didle in the middle\"\nThis indicator is a Hull based keltner channel with the candle colors removed for any close inside the channel.   Good Luck!","id":"01172162-9ff7-4ef1-89e6-81cc30753c34","likes":0,"updated":"2020-05-14T17:24:32.119Z","shares":4872,"trendingScore":1,"usageScore":46,"sources":{"OGCDontDiddle":{"name":"OGCDontDiddle.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Onegreencandle"},{"caption":"NOM Heikin Ashi Smoothed","authorId":137783,"indicators":["NOM Heikin Ashi Smoothed"],"id":"43ebf0f1-35fd-4bf5-a0b7-53a7ddb4559b","text":"Heikin Ashi Smoothed indicator","likes":0,"updated":"2020-07-14T07:22:02.108Z","shares":4769,"trendingScore":11,"usageScore":170,"sources":{"NOMHeikinAshiSmoothed":{"name":"NOMHeikinAshiSmoothed.js"}},"images":[],"author":"nom"},{"caption":"Tiki Awesome Oscillator","indicators":["Tiki Awesome Oscillator"],"authorId":1103,"text":"The Awesome Oscillator is an indicator used to measure market momentum. AO calculates the difference of a 34 Period and 5 Period Simple Moving Averages. The Simple Moving Averages that are used are not calculated using closing price but rather each bar's midpoints. AO is generally used to affirm trends or to anticipate possible reversals.","id":"5b033fd6ba949d00011ae509","updated":"2018-09-24T13:17:07.980Z","likes":0,"shares":4763,"trendingScore":19,"usageScore":364,"sources":{"tikiAwesomeOscillator.js":{"name":"tikiAwesomeOscillator.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"caption":"Tiki VPOC","indicators":["Tiki VPOC"],"authorId":1103,"text":"Plots the VPOC, or the price where most volume traded on a given bar, on bid/ask candlestick charts.","id":"5e6a5e6dea1ab3dfdc5b7c7c","updated":"2020-03-12T16:08:13.401Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":11,"shares":4763,"usageScore":139,"sources":{"tikiVPOC.js":{"name":"tikiVPOC.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"template","module":"funCharts","caption":"CVD + Delta Bars","indicators":[],"authorId":141694,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Used indicators: Volume Delta Grid, VPOC (BAR)","id":"b7a8c80f-4872-4e53-ab5f-d3e80c4e2964","updated":"2021-12-07T16:12:56.353Z","likes":0,"shares":4760,"trendingScore":40,"sources":{"CVD + Delta Bars":{"name":"CVD + Delta Bars.template.tradovate"}},"images":[],"author":"eraser"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"template","module":"funCharts","caption":"entire session","indicators":[],"authorId":234477,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"d31a6fab-066f-4024-bfdc-ca2820d44f2b","text":"Used indicators: VWAP, Volume Profiles","updated":"2021-07-15T19:58:44.134Z","likes":0,"shares":4560,"trendingScore":17,"sources":{"entire session":{"name":"entire session.template.tradovate"}},"images":[],"author":"pri"},{"caption":"Full Stochastic with 80/20 lines","authorId":36652,"indicators":["SLOSTO8020"],"text":"This is the Full Stochastic indicator with 80/20 lines visible.","id":"5c576a2809c13b6ce3f6e697","updated":"2019-02-03T22:28:53.033Z","likes":0,"shares":4519,"trendingScore":19,"usageScore":447,"sources":{"SlowStochastic8020":{"name":"SlowStochastic8020.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Kerell Johnson"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Tiki RSI","entitlement":false,"indicators":["Tiki RSI"],"authorId":1103,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"44d0e564-af4d-4cbb-8205-f8dbe629be0a","text":"This indicator improves on the RSI offered by Tradovate by supporting the Wilders (the recommended moving average) among others.","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2024-11-06T15:51:27.878Z","trendingScore":27,"usageScore":1007,"shares":4454,"sources":{"tikiRSI.js":{"name":"tikiRSI.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"caption":"Tiki Raghee GRaB Candles","indicators":["Tiki Raghee GRaB Candles"],"authorId":1103,"id":"5cbf3385f2813e696363991d","text":"Raghee Horner created this indicator to help her identify when a market is trending (holding above the upper or lower band) or consolidating (chopping inside the band). It consists of a 34 period EMA (which you can override) of the high, low and close. The bars are colored as it traverses across the band to help give you visual cues.","updated":"2019-04-23T15:47:17.950Z","likes":0,"shares":4454,"trendingScore":6,"usageScore":328,"sources":{"tikiGrab.js":{"name":"tikiGrab.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"https://community.tradovate.com/t/ttm-scalper-alert/4202/3","caption":"Tiki Scalper","entitlement":false,"authorId":1103,"indicators":["Tiki Scalper"],"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Based on TTM scalper of John Carter's Scalper Buys and Sells.  The methodology is a close approximation of the one described in his book Mastering the Trade.  Note this does not indicate the trigger bar because it is backward looking.","id":"b914bb76-8de5-4d79-bb00-953e24c41c7d","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2024-11-06T15:58:12.215Z","usageScore":266,"trendingScore":23,"shares":4281,"sources":{"tikiScalper.js":{"name":"tikiScalper.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"caption":"RSI Histogram","authorId":28582,"indicators":["Relative Strength Index - Histogram"],"text":"RSI plotted as a histogram. Adjustable overbought and oversold levels. RSI will take 3 separate colors depending on overbought, oversold, or neither. I use this for RSI-2 with 95 Overbought and 5 Oversold settings. Also includes an EMA of the RSI.","id":"5c05af9a437ff0679686282a","updated":"2019-01-25T16:44:19.574Z","likes":0,"shares":4254,"trendingScore":13,"usageScore":173,"sources":{"rsiHist":{"name":"rsiHist.js"}},"images":[],"author":"mortdiggiddy"},{"caption":"Value Area Levels","authorId":134254,"indicators":["Price Levels"],"text":"This indicator will draw horizontal lines at 6 different levels.  \n\nUseful for those who track Value Area Highs/Lows and the corresponding targets.","id":"c5a30eab-f04d-492a-b3b4-7728e7cb154c","updated":"2020-08-24T04:09:18.827Z","likes":0,"shares":4205,"trendingScore":14,"usageScore":182,"sources":{"PriceLevels":{"name":"PriceLevels.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Donovan Ward"},{"caption":"Liquidity Sweep Reversal","text":"This indicator identifies liquidity sweeps and subsequent reversals on the chart.\n \nA liquidity sweep occurs when price breaks above prior highs (sell-side liquidity) or below prior lows (buy-side liquidity). A reversal is confirmed when price closes in the opposite direction of the sweep, indicating potential trading opportunities.\n\nFeatures:\n- Detects liquidity sweeps above prior highs and below prior lows\n- Identifies reversals when price closes against the sweep direction\n- Displays visual arrows: green triangles pointing up for bullish reversals, red triangles pointing down for bearish reversals\n- Configurable lookback period for sweep detection\n- Consistent arrow sizing for clean visual appearance","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"c88fc1c1-a2b7-4de4-92b1-0a4e0ed79731","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["Smart Liquidity Sweep Reversal"],"authorId":155358,"likes":0,"updated":"2026-03-06T02:19:50.905Z","shares":4072,"trendingScore":146,"usageScore":1988,"sources":{"liquiditySweepReversal.js":{"name":"liquiditySweepReversal.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Vamp"},{"caption":"Heiken Ashi Candle Overlay","authorId":140606,"indicators":["Heikin Ashi Overlay"],"id":"1a5ecfab-2d31-415e-8565-c3aa8acf9692","text":"The values of some indicators change when you use Heikin Ashi candles on Tradovate compared to using Bars or Normal candles.  To remedy this and in collaboration with NOM, this is an overlay that will hide the chart's current bars and draw Heiken Ashi candles on the chart.  This will preserve the values of other indicators affected by differing bar values.","updated":"2020-08-05T15:53:25.952Z","likes":0,"shares":4029,"trendingScore":23,"usageScore":99,"sources":{"heikinAshi_Overlay":{"name":"heikinAshi_Overlay.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Scott K"},{"caption":"LBR_ThreeTenOscillator","indicators":["LBR_ThreeTenOscillator"],"authorId":87472,"id":"1c074e44-5cc7-4646-b137-71ce1cb260f3","text":"The Three Ten Oscillator study comprises four plots, the combination of which is used to determine Buy and Sell signals. These signals are related to two plots of the study: the Fast Line plot and the Slow Line plot. The Fast Line plot shows the difference between the two simple moving averages of price: 3 period and 10 period ones. The Slow Line plot is a slow (16 period) simple moving average of the first plot. When the Fast Line overtakes the Slow Line, it is interpreted as an uptrend, while the Fast Line falling below the Slow Line signifies a downtrend. Thus, the corresponding crossovers of the two plots are considered to indicate Buy and Sell signals. For additional confirmation, the mentioned plots are complemented with Zero Line and Hist plots (the latter represents Fast Line values in the histogram form). Positive values of the histogram confirm the Buy signal and negative values confirm the Sell signal.","updated":"2020-09-02T22:22:21.280Z","likes":0,"shares":4027,"trendingScore":15,"usageScore":210,"sources":{"LBR_ThreeTenOscillator":{"name":"LBR_ThreeTenOscillator.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Sanjay Dubey"},{"caption":"Trafs Ichimoku Cloud","authorId":129881,"indicators":["trafs_Ichimoku"],"text":"Ichimoku Clouds  (inputs: tenkan period (9*)\tThe number of bars used to calculate the Tenkan plot.\nkijun period (26*):\tThe number of bars used to calculate Kijun, Span A, Span B, and Chikou plots.    *default values","id":"9473ec05-a8e9-4fe5-a04e-5a81e871b250","updated":"2020-07-01T09:46:43.333Z","likes":0,"usageScore":157,"shares":4014,"trendingScore":15,"sources":{"trafs-Ichimoku":{"name":"trafs-Ichimoku.js"}},"images":[],"author":"traf nintythree"},{"hidden":false,"caption":"USTsuperTrend","indicators":["SuperTrend"],"authorId":89218,"text":"SuperTrend  indicator optimized!","id":"5d65b142e175e5ce03f1a8c5","updated":"2019-08-27T22:40:02.302Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":12,"usageScore":192,"shares":3993,"sources":{"USTsuperTrend":{"name":"USTsuperTrend.js"}},"images":[],"author":"UpSilonTrading"},{"caption":"FVG Pro","text":"=> Highlights fair value gaps\n=> Looks cool","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"cfcdab32-9266-4e14-9a83-59d0df10d99f","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["~~~FVG Pro~~~"],"authorId":5094514,"likes":0,"updated":"2025-09-01T05:54:11.900Z","trendingScore":197,"usageScore":2623,"shares":3984,"sources":{"FVGpro.js":{"name":"FVGpro.js"}},"images":["809806a0-cfb8-49b9-981c-4f135c07e30b"],"author":"Unlimitidities"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Tiki WAE","entitlement":false,"authorId":1103,"indicators":["Tiki WAE"],"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"The Waddah Attar Explosion Indicator is intended for use by all traders. It merges the Bollinger Bands and MACD together in a special way. This allows it to identify the start of the price explosion situations with very high accuracy. These explosions happen every day and sometimes multiple times a day. By using the Waddah Attar Explosion indicator you can know when this explosion begins and when they end with a high degree of success.","id":"4244080e-c164-45d3-95d8-e5ecd53ebeb1","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2024-11-06T16:05:20.460Z","shares":3953,"trendingScore":18,"usageScore":575,"sources":{"tikiWAE.js":{"name":"tikiWAE.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Latter-day Trader: VWAP Bands","authorId":207522,"indicators":["LDT - VWAP Bands"],"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Added anchored VWAP as an option to NOM VWAP Bands. Also added more bands. Now you can have 6 bands instead of 2. Thanks to NOM and p2f for their original work.","id":"97b6b228-aebf-4da3-b61a-49c9f442eec2","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2021-04-10T16:23:40.576Z","likes":0,"shares":3928,"trendingScore":17,"usageScore":593,"sources":{"LDT_VWAP_BANDS.js":{"name":"LDT_VWAP_BANDS.js"}},"images":[],"author":"LatterDayTrader"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Latter-day Trader: Inside / Outside Bars","indicators":["LDT - Inside / Outside Bars"],"authorId":207522,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Paints inside and outside bars different colors. You have the option to only paint one type or the other or both. Defaults to both.","id":"86b00ae9-4115-4486-96e3-a6e9773480c0","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2021-07-15T22:58:25.760Z","trendingScore":60,"usageScore":2006,"shares":3915,"sources":{"LDT_Inside_Outside_Bars.js":{"name":"LDT_Inside_Outside_Bars.js"}},"images":[],"author":"LatterDayTrader"},{"caption":"Tiki Relative Volume","authorId":1103,"indicators":["Tiki Relative Volume"],"text":"This shows volume at the time of day relative to the prior n periods.  This is very useful in terms of identifying when volume is picking up or slowing down. The absolute value is not as important as whether it is rising or falling.   As participation changes, the price action changes too.  Mahalo to Peter Davies of Jigsaw Trading for this idea!","id":"5a8087872c888a00018b7912","updated":"2018-09-24T13:17:51.350Z","likes":0,"shares":3878,"trendingScore":3,"usageScore":23,"sources":{"tikiRelativeVolume.js":{"name":"tikiRelativeVolume.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"NSDT Zone Predictor Tool","entitlement":false,"indicators":["NSDT Zone Predictor"],"authorId":67660,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"If you use this tool to connect two Pivot Points, it will provide you with a suggested \"Zone\" to trade to and/or through.\n\nAssuming a Long position: You would connect a low pivot point to the next high pivot point and it will draw the potential upper Zone for you. You would then enter a Long position once the high pivot is breached and trade to and/or through the Zone.\n\nAssuming a Short position: You would connect a high pivot point to the next low pivot point and it will draw the potential lower Zone for you. You would then enter a Short position once the low pivot is breached and trade to and/or through the Zone.\n\nFor a more accurate and less risky approach, you would just trade through the Zones.\n\nYou can use this tool on multiple timeframes/instruments. And you can leave the Zones on the chart until they have been breached.","id":"7b8fa60a-4465-43a3-b918-d3a3ff94b5d6","updated":"2022-05-03T15:40:15.914Z","obfuscated":true,"likes":0,"shares":3876,"trendingScore":25,"sources":{"NSDTZonePredictor.js":{"name":"NSDTZonePredictor.js"}},"images":["57219165-1e6c-4bf6-abbe-de36f8d3ed52","7527abc4-c6e2-4625-81e7-7911bb347080","f2eab0f9-1b71-46d2-a8ad-7db20e42560e"],"author":"NorthStarTrading"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"MagnumVision","authorId":72977,"indicators":["magnumstyle"],"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Magnum Vision is a one off indicator meant to help price action traders identify potential pullbacks to zones for entry. Red and Green Boxes are reversals while white boxes are meant to show the highest volume of data loaded.","id":"3ba8805c-f5f4-4b78-94f2-10a76cb17ec0","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2021-09-20T23:00:21.138Z","shares":3817,"trendingScore":18,"usageScore":209,"sources":{"magnumstyle.js":{"name":"magnumstyle.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Proshot"},{"caption":"Tiki Bollinger Bands v2","indicators":["Tiki Bollinger Bands v2"],"authorId":1103,"text":"This update adds the ability to use a different type of moving average calculation.","id":"b6cc0d1a-d4a0-4de6-899e-ec3620bacc32","updated":"2020-05-15T19:41:18.311Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":23,"shares":3800,"usageScore":886,"sources":{"HMA.js":{"name":"HMA.js"},"tikiBollingerBands2.js":{"name":"tikiBollingerBands2.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Fibonacci Retracement Tool by 4C (v3.0)","entitlement":false,"indicators":["FIBS_4C (v3.0)"],"authorId":172419,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"This is a major update replacing the previous version on 09/19/24.\n\nThis Fibonacci Retracement Tool has been redesigned for Tradovate to \"correctly\" draw fib retracements and resolve the issue where the stock fib tool plotted percentage levels upside down (compared to most platforms). It also provides customizable levels, including 'negative' values used as profit targets in Fibonacci extensions and measured moves.\n\nKey Updates:\nEnhanced Level Customization: Reduced from 15 to 11 levels, each with independent toggles for visibility, color, and opacity.\nImproved Code Efficiency: More efficient handling of levels and colors.\nSettings Layout Cleanup: Organized for easier use.\nVisual Shading Between Levels: Improved visual clarity for retracement zones.","id":"6a64a007-d6ba-4c97-b567-529e95de92a9","updated":"2024-09-19T17:53:23.876Z","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"shares":3701,"trendingScore":58,"sources":{"FIBS_4C_v3.js":{"name":"FIBS_4C_v3.js"}},"images":["571ee1bc-1d4d-46db-9b5b-023e865afae6","7ce63b76-9c04-4552-9a23-055f6af28f11"],"author":"FourC"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"https://community.tradovate.com/t/footprintcandles-overlay/9003","caption":"FootprintCandles","entitlement":false,"indicators":["FootprintCandles"],"authorId":753811,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"A footprint overlay for candlesticks. It allows you to see areas of high buying or selling. \n\nIf “absolute high deltas” is off, the highlighted delta zones will be based on the average of the “delta lookback” period and the “contrast” which is how close the current bar’s delta is to the absolute delta MA (lookback). It is recommended to keep “absolute high deltas” and “only high deltas” on and just adjust “tick resolution” and “absolute high delta value” for the specific instrument.\n\nThere are some slight rounding errors when tick resolution is too large relative to total ticks per candle because of the way the data is aggregated, but it works well enough.\n\nZoom in to see delta values text.","id":"47a11fa9-2fd5-4657-ac2e-45b47cf0ee77","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2024-03-21T20:12:05.976Z","trendingScore":82,"usageScore":67,"shares":3677,"sources":{"FootprintCandles":{"name":"FootprintCandles"}},"images":["94faf674-3a56-42c5-a28f-40dd740f86bd","a3ea53ca-9808-4443-a0d8-937f27e73f24","ddcaffe0-c3bf-47c4-9d20-bdd5c995dc62"],"author":"ekb"},{"caption":"Tick Count","authorId":28582,"indicators":["Ticks"],"text":"Shows colored histogram of the ticks for each candle. The ticks are normalized to a percent of 0 - 100 of the EMA of the historical candle ticks. When used on a tick chart, the indicator can be used as a progress indicator as to how many ticks have been counted on the current candle. ","id":"5c0c1593d5e48602cde8a4fd","updated":"2018-12-10T16:38:00.299Z","likes":0,"shares":3638,"trendingScore":6,"usageScore":21,"sources":{"ticks":{"name":"ticks.js"}},"images":[],"author":"mortdiggiddy"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Latter-day Trader: TTM Squeeze Cloud","indicators":["LDT - TTM Squeeze Cloud"],"authorId":207522,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"0a964443-fd47-4eb6-9e1b-09582f76f802","text":"Displays the TTM Squeeze as a cloud. \n\nMade famous by John Carter, this uses Bollinger Bands and Keltner Channels. When the BBands are inside the Keltners, it suggests that the price action is in period of consolidation or a squeeze. \n\nBased on the settings you use, you can decide what constitutes a squeeze. For example, a smaller ATR multiplier would result in less squeezes.","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2021-06-05T02:31:40.701Z","likes":0,"usageScore":268,"shares":3621,"trendingScore":14,"sources":{"HMA.js":{"name":"HMA.js"},"LDT_Squeeze_Cloud.js":{"name":"LDT_Squeeze_Cloud.js"},"intersect.js":{"name":"intersect.js"},"maHelpers.js":{"name":"maHelpers.js"}},"images":[],"author":"LatterDayTrader"},{"caption":"Tiki ADX","authorId":1103,"indicators":["Tiki ADX"],"text":"Enhanced the native ADX indicator to paint the bars/candlesticks according to the current positive/negative trend, and added an adjustable signal line as an indicator for trend status.","id":"5d0111334f08ed4b64ea960e","updated":"2019-06-12T14:50:27.732Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":11,"shares":3592,"usageScore":305,"sources":{"tikiADX.js":{"name":"tikiADX.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"https://community.tradovate.com/t/fibonacci-negative-values/1321/7","caption":"Improved Fibonacci Retracement","entitlement":false,"indicators":["+Fibonacci Retracement"],"authorId":285399,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Fully customizable Fibonacci Retracement drawing tool. You can define up to 16 points and colors (down to a minimum value of -4.618). Handles negative numbers, up-trend and down-trend markets. \n\nTo customize the drawing, first use the tool to draw a preliminary drawing, then double-click to modify the parameters.\n\n(Note: this tool relies on the 0% and 100% values for anchor points. While you can remove those points, it may be awkward to create the drawing without them. For the best experience with this tool, it is suggested that you keep the 0% and 100% points.)","id":"afe0038b-8765-4d83-ba45-8a142e561dd5","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2021-12-27T12:30:01.386Z","trendingScore":29,"shares":3437,"sources":{"FibRetracement.js":{"name":"FibRetracement.js"}},"images":["45e08ac8-8af8-4b26-89fb-ffe4f4a13814","d4e4b8c1-49cd-4919-b48f-ae2356149d52"],"author":"alennert"},{"caption":"VWAP & Market Structure: A Data-Driven Approach","text":"The MultiPeriodVWAP script calculates Anchored VWAPs for multiple timeframes—yearly, monthly, weekly, daily, and futures open—to track market sentiment and dynamic support/resistance levels.\n\nHow it Works:\n✅ VWAP resets at key times:\n\nYearly (Jan 1), Monthly (1st of month), Weekly (Sunday 6 PM Futures Open), Daily (9:30 AM NY Open), Futures Open (6 PM NY).\n✅ Tracks session high/low & updates VWAP dynamically using volume-weighted price sums.\n✅ Determines control:\nAbove VWAP? Bullish Bias\nBelow VWAP? Bearish Bias\nNear VWAP? Consolidation\nUsed by institutions & traders for trend tracking, reversals, and key entry points. VWAP & Market Structure: Brian Shannon’s Approach\nManually add an anchored VWAP to the previous 24-hour high and low for day trading structure. Tradovate is lacking a point-and-click anchored VWAP like all their competitors have.","updated":"2025-02-16T20:26:40.071Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"cb137108-95eb-4114-a82d-daa79a992902","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["Anchored VWAPs with various anchoring periods (yearly, monthly, weekly, daily, futures open)."],"authorId":2219171,"likes":0,"trendingScore":54,"usageScore":541,"shares":3432,"sources":{"VWAPYEARMONTHWEEKNIGHTDAY.js":{"name":"VWAPYEARMONTHWEEKNIGHTDAY.js"}},"images":[],"author":"servantthought"},{"caption":"Range Forecast","indicators":["Range Forecast"],"authorId":28582,"text":"Plots two horizontal lines above and below a Momentum Range or Range candle to show the price that must be reached in order to close the current candle and begin a new candle. Range charts differ from Momentum Range charts in that the next open is always 1 tick above/below the close value of the previous candle. This script will figure that out automatically. This is similar to the Tiki Range Forecast script but removes the bug where there would be multiple historical dots displayed... and horizontal lines are better suited instead of dots. Only one set of horizontal lines are displayed at any given moment.","id":"5c1a77dbd5e486cd4be8a82f","updated":"2018-12-19T16:54:51.446Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":11,"shares":3407,"usageScore":225,"sources":{"rangeForecast":{"name":"rangeForecast.js"}},"images":[],"author":"mortdiggiddy"},{"caption":"Delta Candle","authorId":87472,"indicators":["Delta Candle"],"id":"67b103c0-31b2-4d4e-9028-e7ea1a851165","text":"Delta is a key concept to understand when making trading decisions based upon traded volume.It’s the difference between the volume of market orders buying by lifting the offer price and the volume of market orders selling by hitting the bid price.In other words, if Delta is greater than zero, we had more buying than selling and if Delta is less than zero, we had more selling than buying.Delta gives us a broad sense for each bar of whether we have more aggressive buying or selling.\nThis indicator plots delta candlestick on the chart & OHLC of delta on data box. Historical data doesn't contains sequence of the volumes, so you won't see high and low of delta for historical data. It's going to show candlestick delta chart only if you have it open.","likes":0,"updated":"2020-08-26T11:08:13.858Z","trendingScore":4,"shares":3375,"usageScore":23,"sources":{"deltaCandle":{"name":"deltaCandle.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Sanjay Dubey"},{"caption":"Risk/Reward Tool","text":"This is a Risk Reward tool similar to other platforms. To use click on entry point, drag up/down to set Stop Loss risk, click to set, then drag up/down to set Target. Once set you may adjust using the anchors. Tradovate doesn’t do well with “AutoDetect” a chart’s instrument so it’s best to set the instrument in the settings dialog dropdown to get the correct tick size, dollar amount per tick, etc.","updated":"2025-11-27T14:42:41.625Z","link":"https://community.tradovate.com/t/risk-rewardtool/12409","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"457f8028-8a78-4f2a-9b85-91cb2fc362b5","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["Risk Reward Tool"],"authorId":5564593,"likes":0,"usageScore":0,"shares":3374,"trendingScore":180,"sources":{"RiskRewardTool.js":{"name":"RiskRewardTool.js"}},"images":["8ab999d7-fde1-4e58-8d44-5608e4013ddc","bcf62a88-42e3-4904-9178-82e1bd547391","ccb93b93-7a69-4e7c-8d81-e9c543bd2191"],"author":"jrenza"},{"caption":"mph Tick Counter","indicators":["[mph] Tick Countdown"],"authorId":121424,"text":"Counts down the number of ticks left in a bar on a tick chart.\n\nVery Important! DO NOT check the \"Show Value\" box in the preferences. \n\nWhy? This indicator relies on using an artifical value always within one tick of the price to keep the text on the chart constantly updating, without trying to autofit the number of ticks onto the chart. If you show the value, the indicator will cover the current price with this value.\n\n===========================\n\nCopyright 2020 Michael Hines\nPermission to use this software is granted under the MIT License. A copy is included in the source code.\n\nYou alone are responsibile for your trading. Futures carry a substantial risk of loss.\n\nThe developer is not a financial advisor, and does not claim that the software provided or calculations made by it are suitable for use as or in part of financial advice. Any statements or descriptions of use of the software by the developer are solely the opinion of the developer, and should not be relied on as or in part of financial advice.","id":"5e94d29d5fd18d244159ae1c","updated":"2020-04-13T20:59:09.117Z","likes":0,"usageScore":156,"trendingScore":7,"shares":3369,"sources":{"mphTickCountdown":{"name":"mphTickCountdown.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Michael Hines"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Latter-day Trader: Colorful MA WonderCloud (v2)","indicators":["LDT - Colorful MA WonderCloud (v2)"],"authorId":207522,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"7ebccad6-ae0e-4c66-9a1b-c9afbec82235","text":"New and slightly improved version. The cloud is now smoother and prettier. No more rounded edges when you zoom in. Also added KAMA as a Fast line option. \n\nThis Uses the new Graphics api, specifically the Polygon DisplayObject type.  It only works with new charts. Legacy charts are NOT supported.","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"entitlement":false,"updated":"2022-11-13T03:12:45.427Z","shares":3349,"trendingScore":10,"usageScore":649,"sources":{"LDT_Colorful_WonderCloud_v2.js":{"name":"LDT_Colorful_WonderCloud_v2.js"}},"images":[],"author":"LatterDayTrader"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"template","module":"funCharts","caption":"Scalpert 5 minute VolPro","indicators":[],"authorId":114965,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Used indicators: VWAP, p2f - Dead Simple Reversal, Volume Profiles, NOM VWAP Bands, Tiki OHLC","id":"917dff53-3c47-4c5d-b6d9-29ee7b09ec40","updated":"2022-03-05T04:13:35.173Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":19,"shares":3211,"sources":{"Scalpert 5 minute VolPro":{"name":"Scalpert 5 minute VolPro.template.tradovate"}},"images":[],"author":"Scalpert"},{"hidden":