tochastic","indicators":["Tiki Stochastic"],"authorId":1103,"text":"This indicator improves upon Tradovate's native Stochastic indicator by adding overbought/oversold lines, and separate periods for calculating K, smoothing K, and the D trigger.  It also supports different moving average types.","id":"5e7a3c1a454abdf3c1a5fca9","updated":"2020-03-24T16:58:02.868Z","likes":0,"shares":3058,"trendingScore":6,"usageScore":236,"sources":{"HMA.js":{"name":"HMA.js"},"tikiStochastic.js":{"name":"tikiStochastic.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"https://community.tradovate.com/t/delta-by-price-indicator/3209/57","caption":"Variable Resolution Bid Ask Delta","entitlement":false,"indicators":["Variable Resolution Delta"],"authorId":285399,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"8d14a7cb-6163-4af6-9c1c-0c1b6c872b7b","text":"Bid Ask Delta per bar, but you can set the Prices Per Level property to combine data for multiple price levels. Good for markets with large tick ranges - makes Bid Ask Deltas readable on charts for NQ and YM.","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2022-01-14T16:55:06.015Z","likes":0,"shares":3043,"trendingScore":14,"usageScore":124,"sources":{"bidAskRes.js":{"name":"bidAskRes.js"}},"images":["6cbcaba2-3c2f-48c3-8653-9ff2b33a4959","eabfe18f-1a73-4191-b627-993f3b0f3ae0"],"author":"alennert"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Fibonacci Pivot Points v1","authorId":187183,"indicators":["Fibonacci Pivot Points v1"],"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"a469d14b-21e2-435c-9f31-5d534151a833","text":"Fibonacci Pivot Points","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2021-06-10T14:28:52.615Z","shares":3030,"trendingScore":20,"usageScore":138,"sources":{"bnotb_Fibonacci_Pivots_v1.js":{"name":"bnotb_Fibonacci_Pivots_v1.js"}},"images":[],"author":"bnotb"},{"caption":"Ichimoku","authorId":134482,"indicators":["Ichimoku"],"id":"60c7d1aa-5ab3-42be-be99-5d5a89ad9432","text":"Ichimoku Indicator","updated":"2020-05-30T03:10:16.269Z","likes":0,"shares":3012,"trendingScore":19,"usageScore":21,"sources":{"USTichimoku":{"name":"USTichimoku.js"}},"images":[],"author":"UpSilonTrading"},{"caption":"Tiki True Strength Index","indicators":["Tiki True Strength Index"],"authorId":1103,"text":"The TSI fluctuates between positive and negative territory. Positive territory means the bulls are more in control of the asset. Negative territory means the bears are more in control. When the indicator divergences with price, that may signal the price trend is weakening and may reverse. A signal line can be applied to the TSI indicator. When the TSI crosses above the signal line it can be used as a buy signal, and when it crosses below, a sell signal. Such crossovers occur frequently so use with caution.","id":"5de97f06f9ae8445cb87cdc0","updated":"2019-12-05T22:04:54.308Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":19,"usageScore":211,"shares":2997,"sources":{"tikiTrueStrengthIndex.js":{"name":"tikiTrueStrengthIndex.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"caption":"Improved Tiki Trend","indicators":["tystr - Improved Tiki Trend"],"authorId":136130,"text":"This indicator improves upon the Tiki Trend indicator by allowing you to configure the color of the bars.","id":"283614a1-e002-4b0d-8d31-508925fb680d","updated":"2020-10-06T21:57:05.835Z","likes":0,"shares":2973,"trendingScore":0,"usageScore":189,"sources":{"tystrImprovedTikiTrend":{"name":"tystrImprovedTikiTrend.js"}},"images":[],"author":"tystr"},{"caption":"Tiki VWMA","indicators":["Tiki VWMA"],"authorId":1103,"text":"The VWMA, or Volume Weighted Moving Average, multiplies volume by price to attain a moving average that incorporates volume into the calculation. It is commonly used as a confirming indicator along with other moving averages, giving confidence a price move is supported by volume.","id":"5af322cf8b4ef200011caa1f","updated":"2018-09-24T13:18:12.259Z","likes":0,"shares":2916,"trendingScore":7,"usageScore":193,"sources":{"tikiVWMA.js":{"name":"tikiVWMA.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Recent Bid/Ask Volume","entitlement":false,"authorId":120687,"indicators":["Recent Bid/Ask Volume"],"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"0e51b649-8e81-485a-90b6-842f60eaa8ef","text":"Shows the recent bid/ask volume like Jigsaw/SierraChart does in a DOM column.","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2023-01-31T15:43:53.617Z","trendingScore":20,"shares":2876,"usageScore":92,"sources":{"PriceAxisDelta.js":{"name":"PriceAxisDelta.js"}},"images":[],"author":"goldenfibs"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Sethmo Delta Histogram","entitlement":false,"authorId":130646,"indicators":["Sethmo Delta Histogram"],"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"be810e53-e251-4e63-9484-a5120f2da132","text":"Modified version of Sanjay Dubey's Delta Histogram, but added option to invert price axis and also parameters to change the delta candle color.","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2022-02-27T21:10:33.238Z","shares":2846,"trendingScore":19,"usageScore":419,"sources":{"sethmodeltaHistogram.js":{"name":"sethmodeltaHistogram.js"}},"images":["146b289b-a3fc-46f7-a722-8ac1cc7ab26e","9842091b-80ab-4b33-8582-8012a9a4c30c"],"author":"Seth Mo"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"p2f - Hull Moving Average Turning Points","authorId":138571,"indicators":["p2f - HMA Turning Points"],"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"A port of Seth Urion's HMA turning points indicator, this notes changes in the rate of change of a Hull moving average, to show early signs of a changing trend.","id":"8cdec229-0445-42c7-b242-01290923cf8e","updated":"2021-07-06T00:23:42.981Z","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"shares":2830,"trendingScore":3,"usageScore":518,"sources":{"p2fHMATurningPoints.js":{"name":"p2fHMATurningPoints.js"}},"images":[],"author":"paidtofade"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"https://community.tradovate.com/t/check-out-new-delta-highlighter-indicator/8613","caption":"Delta Highlighter","entitlement":false,"indicators":["Delta Highlighter"],"authorId":753811,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Color your candles by delta! Highlight potential strong market sentiment, absorption, and trapped traders.","id":"b879bb2e-4bfc-4d0d-b69b-3ac00d9a91fa","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2024-02-22T01:46:31.863Z","trendingScore":41,"usageScore":159,"shares":2829,"sources":{"DeltaHighlighter.js":{"name":"DeltaHighlighter.js"}},"images":["3271438e-b357-4702-aaac-067a8163671b","a2679497-6fb2-4d8a-97db-0cbf4d0f823a","e34e7925-fed7-495a-84a6-90ce34bb4995"],"author":"ekb"},{"caption":"Volume Imbalance","text":"Based on TraderOracle's Volume Imbalances indicator, volume imbalances, also known as candle gaps, detect gaps between consecutive candles of the same colour. This is plotted as a horizontal line marking the imbalance until the price returns to fill the void.","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"e586c7ec-a50a-4d47-85e6-22f80e2b05dd","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["Volume Imbalance"],"authorId":2584109,"likes":0,"updated":"2025-04-23T22:43:33.330Z","trendingScore":33,"usageScore":1265,"shares":2810,"sources":{"volumeImbalance.js":{"name":"volumeImbalance.js"}},"images":[],"author":"James I"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"ATR Fibonacci Trail Stop","indicators":["ATR Fibonacci Trail"],"authorId":187183,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"f95d7b7f-27a6-408d-abb6-c298b5358e08","text":"This indicator is bassed on the Community Indicator: \"ATR TrailStop w/Fib Target Prices\".\n\nThis indicator focuses on the ATR Trail Stop and expands on the Fibonacci levels above/below it. The ATR Trail Stop itself is always your 100% level, and the furthest price away is always your 0% level. Levels in between adjust accordingly.","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2021-05-28T20:16:08.440Z","likes":0,"shares":2795,"trendingScore":11,"usageScore":193,"sources":{"bnotb_ATR_Fibonacci_Trail.js":{"name":"bnotb_ATR_Fibonacci_Trail.js"}},"images":["11f5d15c-84b3-407b-98f8-df6d434bde02"],"author":"bnotb"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Volume Spikes","entitlement":false,"indicators":["Volume Spikes"],"authorId":317781,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"A volume histogram that highlights bars when they are above a simple moving average threshold. The threshold is defined at a number of standard deviations from the moving average. For visual reference, bands are plotted at 1, 2, and 3 standard deviations from the moving average.","id":"c96aca3e-5bfa-4672-b06d-85df00681fb2","updated":"2023-02-24T06:06:22.368Z","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"shares":2775,"trendingScore":27,"usageScore":353,"sources":{"volumeSpikes.js":{"name":"volumeSpikes.js"}},"images":["cb2546b0-3b7a-4db7-997e-85254f309368","e0bda442-69e4-4afc-ab56-1242e30c3a48"],"author":"NCX"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"RSI","entitlement":false,"indicators":["Relative Strength Index with Smooth MA and Histogram"],"authorId":2447526,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"RSI with Smooth MA","id":"f53dc889-2890-49e3-b5a7-482831fea97f","updated":"2024-04-08T01:02:59.382Z","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"shares":2750,"trendingScore":60,"usageScore":403,"sources":{"RSIwithSnoothMA.js":{"name":"RSIwithSnoothMA.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Pnguyen"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"https://community.tradovate.com/t/delta-by-price-indicator/3209/21","caption":"Price Axis Volume Delta Preview","entitlement":false,"indicators":["Price Axis Volume Delta"],"authorId":285399,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"8c758848-1ff0-46d2-b7f2-a21f357a01ab","text":"*For the Trader Web Application. Future updates will be announced for standalone versions and for parameterized delta resolutions.*\n\nAn indicator that shows the delta volume on the Price axis of a chart. Operates on a per-tick basis to show accurate data about the delta volume at a given price.","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2021-12-21T18:30:20.373Z","shares":2735,"trendingScore":7,"usageScore":138,"sources":{"PriceAxisDelta.js":{"name":"PriceAxisDelta.js"}},"images":["27e6670d-ad6d-4c50-b7fb-b75b3c3c9ba4","3c9d7336-d6dd-4e6d-afa0-82cda47ae8e9"],"author":"alennert"},{"caption":"marketorderbubbles","text":"big trades","updated":"2025-10-10T20:05:35.957Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"6f46be90-b557-4987-a439-cf80bb56e05d","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["Displays bubbles for large market orders on the chart in real-time."],"authorId":4348008,"likes":0,"trendingScore":90,"usageScore":357,"shares":2718,"sources":{"marketorderbubbles.js":{"name":"marketorderbubbles.js"}},"images":[],"author":"philicioustrades"},{"caption":"OGC Trend Friend","indicators":["OGC Trend Friend"],"authorId":86160,"text":"This indicator is helps you find a change in trend and to stay in a trade until the trend weakens or hits an upper range.  Best use with tick charts.  Good Luck!","id":"f3695caa-cbbf-4e8a-89a3-a01d26bccae9","updated":"2020-05-12T11:37:38.642Z","likes":0,"shares":2668,"trendingScore":-9,"usageScore":138,"sources":{"OGCMomentumRangeOscillator":{"name":"OGCMomentumRangeOscillator.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Onegreencandle"},{"caption":"Standard Deviation with Volatility","indicators":["Std. Dev Volatility"],"authorId":133784,"id":"b00d7b08-f9bf-4562-a3b1-df20ac7b1f6b","text":"This indicator will calculated the projected moves for the day based on Standard Deviations, Fibonacci, and Volatility. Requires the input of index settlement price found on CME Website, along with the VIX/VXN closing price. These values will need to be updated at market close (5pm est) for each day.","likes":0,"updated":"2020-09-09T14:37:26.935Z","usageScore":113,"shares":2664,"trendingScore":20,"sources":{"VixPredict":{"name":"VixPredict.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Patocalypse"},{"caption":"Tiki Better Volume","authorId":1103,"indicators":["Tiki Better Volume"],"id":"3eeaead1-f32c-49cc-9f17-6ff36d7b07e4","text":"Market tops are characterized by Volume Climax Up bars, High Volume Churn and Low Volume Up bars (also called Testing).\n\nMarket bottoms are characterized by Volume Climax Down bars, High Volume Churn and Low Volume Down bars (Testing).\n\nPullbacks, in either up or down trends, are similar to market topping or bottoming patterns, but shorter in duration and with simpler volume patterns.","updated":"2021-01-07T18:20:55.677Z","likes":0,"shares":2635,"trendingScore":18,"usageScore":225,"sources":{"tikiBetterVolume.js":{"name":"tikiBetterVolume.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"caption":"Tiki Money Flow Index","indicators":["Tiki Money Flow Index"],"authorId":1103,"text":"The Money Flow Index (MFI) is a technical oscillator that uses price and volume for identifying overbought or oversold conditions in an asset. It can also be used to spot divergences which warn of a trend change in price. The oscillator moves between 0 and 100.","id":"5e796961755aee49f2b20a32","updated":"2020-03-24T01:58:57.198Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":6,"usageScore":153,"shares":2635,"sources":{"tikiMFI.js":{"name":"tikiMFI.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"caption":"Buy/Sell Dots","text":"My interpretation of TraderOracle's buy/sell signals.","updated":"2025-03-24T05:10:14.923Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"0ae8b5f9-8110-4f94-9036-af2fb9b5e180","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["Buy/Sell Dots"],"authorId":2584109,"likes":0,"trendingScore":64,"usageScore":902,"shares":2629,"sources":{"buySellDots.js":{"name":"buySellDots.js"}},"images":[],"author":"James I"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Triple Exponential Moving Average","authorId":214672,"indicators":["Triple Exponential Moving Average"],"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"58cbad3e-58fd-40e6-be5c-aa5fc97ed5b9","text":"Triple Exponential Moving Average (TEMA) = (3∗EMA1​)−(3∗EMA2​)+EMA3​\n\nUseful as it responds to price action faster than EMA","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2021-03-26T16:23:38.234Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":33,"usageScore":794,"shares":2609,"sources":{"TEMA.js":{"name":"TEMA.js"}},"images":[],"author":"KalD"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"CPR","indicators":["CPR"],"authorId":72977,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Central Pivot Range calculated with the High, Low, Close values of the previous day gives the trader an indication of potentially trending or non-trending days in the market. When the Pivots are close together it is said that the market is going to be potentially trending, when spread apart the market will be sideways.","id":"d2e26254-ef51-4db2-8a51-905f5512d92a","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2021-08-17T22:47:23.704Z","shares":2576,"trendingScore":19,"usageScore":252,"sources":{"CPR.js":{"name":"CPR.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Proshot"},{"caption":"Tiki Relative Volume Histogram","authorId":1103,"indicators":["Tiki Relative Volume Histogram"],"text":"This is the histogram version of the Tiki Relative Volume study.","id":"5afce911273acc00019abdf2","updated":"2018-09-24T13:17:55.154Z","likes":0,"shares":2544,"trendingScore":-4,"usageScore":12,"sources":{"tikiRelativeVolumeHistogram.js":{"name":"tikiRelativeVolumeHistogram.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"template","module":"funCharts","caption":"the setup","indicators":[],"authorId":321142,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"48ce158c-3b35-4c1e-b3f7-12ef3caa3f20","text":"Used indicators: Cumulative Delta, VWAP, p2f - Adaptive Moving Average, Volume Profiles, NOM VWAP Bands","updated":"2022-01-13T19:51:07.196Z","likes":0,"shares":2535,"trendingScore":8,"sources":{"the setup":{"name":"the setup.template.tradovate"}},"images":[],"author":"Aidan Makled"},{"entityType":"chartIndicator","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"indicators":["Time Frame High / Low"],"likes":0,"authorId":6226137,"updated":"2025-12-27T22:31:51.283Z","link":"","obfuscated":false,"id":"83f507a4-5641-496b-9053-999376d179ac","text":"This Time Frame High / Low indicator is meant to allow you to create any high or low you would like. The purpose is to be able to create session highs and lows, NY open to close, Asia session high and lows, London etc. Or use it to create ORBs for sessions. Anything that requires a high and low you can set; you also can set the end time so that it stops showing after that point. It will only do one day and reset for the next day though. Not for weekly or monthly high or lows.","caption":"Time Frame High and Low Indicator","entitlement":false,"trendingScore":116,"usageScore":1103,"shares":2533,"sources":{"TimeFrameHighLow.js":{"name":"TimeFrameHighLow.js"}},"images":["3e4680c0-cdda-4822-bc6d-7f5b9008fcb5"],"author":"Jspiel"},{"caption":"Tiki Heiken Ashi Differential","indicators":["Tiki Heiken Ashi Differential"],"authorId":1103,"text":"This indicator is used quantify Heikin Ashi candles, and measures the difference between the HA close and HA open. By default, a configurable smoothing 3 period SMA is used as a crossover or trigger. The zero line is also important, and gives further indication on the strength of the trend.","id":"5c492d8291564e0d21699452","updated":"2019-01-30T17:45:08.321Z","likes":0,"shares":2529,"trendingScore":3,"usageScore":47,"sources":{"tikiHeikenAshiDifferential.js":{"name":"tikiHeikenAshiDifferential.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"caption":"Tiki Ultimate Oscillator","indicators":["Tiki Ultimate Oscillator"],"authorId":1103,"text":"A technical indicator invented by Larry Williams that uses the weighted average of three different time periods to reduce the volatility and false transaction signals that are associated with many other indicators that mainly rely on a single time period.","id":"5a09f84daabd350001b0a8ca","updated":"2018-09-24T13:18:06.672Z","likes":0,"shares":2510,"trendingScore":-2,"usageScore":31,"sources":{"tikiUltimateOsc.js":{"name":"tikiUltimateOsc.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"entityType":"template","module":"funCharts","caption":"Fractal Scalp","indicators":[],"authorId":186417,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":false,"id":"96504b17-8c2a-4987-abfa-7ca3622adb58","text":"Used indicators: Moving Average - w/Trend Color, LDT - Williams Fractals, Relative Strength Index","updated":"2021-05-31T16:08:16.424Z","likes":0,"hidden":false,"shares":2506,"trendingScore":16,"sources":{"Fractal Scalp":{"name":"Fractal Scalp.template.tradovate"}},"images":[],"author":"Otto Blink"},{"caption":"Tiki On Balance Volume","indicators":["Tiki On Balance Volume"],"authorId":1103,"text":"On Balance Volume keeps a running total of volume flowing into or out of a product. When the security closes higher than the previous close, all of the period's volume is considered up-volume. A close lower than the previous period results in all of the period's volume considered down-volume. A rising OBV is defined as a sign of smart money flowing into a product. As the public then moves into the product, both the product and the OBV will surge ahead. If price movement precedes OBV movement, it is called a \"non-confirmation.\" Non-confirmations can occur at bull market tops, when the product rises before/without the OBV or at bear market bottoms when the security falls before/without the OBV.\n\nLook for rising trends (when each new peak is higher than the previous peak and each new trough is higher than the previous trough) or falling trends (when each successive peak is lower than the previous peak and each successive trough is lower than the previous trough) to signal a \"breakout.\" ","id":"5c2e1d953ed3be8f8ea3ebf9","updated":"2019-01-03T14:35:01.581Z","likes":0,"shares":2501,"trendingScore":-1,"usageScore":59,"sources":{"tikiOnBalanceVolume.js":{"name":"tikiOnBalanceVolume.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"caption":"Stochastic with the 20 and 80 lines","indicators":["STO"],"authorId":4258,"text":"Stochastic with the 20 and 80 lines","id":"5bea690c231e4897c224aa9a","updated":"2018-11-13T06:02:52.486Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":11,"shares":2487,"usageScore":97,"sources":{"stochastic_lines":{"name":"stochastic_lines.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Bastiaan"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Bid Ask Volume Histogram","entitlement":false,"authorId":120687,"indicators":["BidAskVolume"],"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"53daf194-6e66-4c49-976c-1d346e1a670f","text":"Histogram that shows the bid and ask volume bars separately. Intended for footprint charts.","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2023-01-09T00:10:21.702Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":12,"shares":2485,"usageScore":98,"sources":{"BidAskVolumeBars.js":{"name":"BidAskVolumeBars.js"}},"images":[],"author":"goldenfibs"},{"caption":"MY STRATEGY 28.04.2025","text":"Order flow + value area","updated":"2025-04-28T08:21:35.613Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":false,"id":"4d00a01b-322c-495b-9281-abe37099a357","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["Orderflow Rectangle and Value Area Rectangle"],"authorId":4544779,"likes":0,"hidden":false,"trendingScore":47,"usageScore":406,"shares":2460,"sources":{"mystrategy.js":{"name":"mystrategy.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Jakub Koval"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Three Moving Averages","indicators":["ThreeMA"],"authorId":186417,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"5b6dc795-efdd-4166-892a-b63d1a8f9745","text":"Three moving averages in one indicator. Multiple MA choices and inputs are available.","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2021-06-24T16:48:40.895Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":6,"shares":2442,"usageScore":400,"sources":{"ThreeMA.js":{"name":"ThreeMA.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Otto Blink"},{"caption":"Tiki Linear Regression Curve","authorId":1103,"indicators":["Tiki Linear Regression Curve"],"text":"The Linear Regression Curve plots a line that best fits the prices specified over a user-defined time period. Think of the Linear Regression Curve as numerous lines, but both extreme ends of the lines are hidden, while the center portion is shown and is connected to other center portions of lines. The Linear Regression Curve is used mainly to identify trend direction and might sometimes be used to generate buy and sell signals.","id":"5af04fead9a01100011bdf38","updated":"2018-09-24T13:17:25.283Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":5,"usageScore":92,"shares":2419,"sources":{"tikiLinearRegressionCurve.js":{"name":"tikiLinearRegressionCurve.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"caption":"Tiki Keltner Channel","authorId":1103,"id":"6d9a3ad8-e64b-4d85-aa06-4ed616a61ac4","text":"Keltner Channels are volatility-based envelopes set above and below an exponential moving average. This indicator is similar to Bollinger Bands, which use the standard deviation to set the bands. Instead of using the standard deviation, Keltner Channels use the Average True Range (ATR) to set channel distance. ","likes":0,"indicators":["Tiki Keltner Channels"],"updated":"2020-05-22T14:48:46.507Z","trendingScore":11,"shares":2414,"usageScore":147,"sources":{"HMA.js":{"name":"HMA.js"},"tikiKeltnerChannels.js":{"name":"tikiKeltnerChannels.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"caption":"Order block indicator","text":"find order blocks for you","updated":"2025-08-29T01:29:23.457Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"59076f2f-35d9-4660-b7bf-912c896739d1","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["order block"],"authorId":5353814,"likes":0,"shares":2392,"trendingScore":43,"usageScore":610,"sources":{"orderblock.js":{"name":"orderblock.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Devon Plasterer"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"workspace","caption":"Orderflow_Multi","indicators":[],"authorId":1549794,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Used modules: Chart, DOM\nUsed indicators: Volume Delta Grid, Moving Average Convergence Divergence\nTheme: dark","id":"8e1a809c-852a-4588-bb6e-0812060e1d96","updated":"2023-10-29T19:42:10.519Z","likes":0,"shares":2387,"trendingScore":46,"sources":{"Orderflow_Multi":{"name":"Orderflow_Multi.workspace.tradovate"}},"images":[],"author":"JMBneverSLEEPS"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"https://community.tradovate.com/t/new-sessiondeltaprofile/9043","caption":"SessionDeltaProfile","entitlement":false,"indicators":["SessionDeltaProfile"],"authorId":753811,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"I was able to convert the price axis delta tool to be configurable by time. You can select time, tick resolution, and color options, as well as the ability to automatically change resolution based on zoom level.\n\n-note: it takes a second to load, be patient","id":"f8fb9002-cb39-46cd-9ba3-6034aedef702","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2024-04-22T14:08:06.852Z","shares":2379,"trendingScore":36,"usageScore":138,"sources":{"SessionDeltaProfile":{"name":"SessionDeltaProfile"}},"images":["56503520-3a89-4cad-b1a9-1e805d8f894e","9a618ca6-7ffd-42c3-90db-2dd04fca642a","b7644d7c-9339-4dfd-93f6-b26e3674da9e"],"author":"ekb"},{"caption":"Tiki VWAP MPD","indicators":["Tiki VWAP MPD"],"authorId":1103,"text":"The MPD (Maximum Permissible Deviation) bands are added to the VWAP to help provide a dynamic range useful especially in choppy conditions.","id":"5dfba7ccddf139f3c8bbcace","updated":"2019-12-19T16:39:40.309Z","likes":0,"shares":2330,"trendingScore":8,"usageScore":112,"sources":{"tikiMPD.js":{"name":"tikiMPD.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"caption":"Tiki DEMA","indicators":["Tiki Double EMA"],"authorId":1103,"text":"The DEMA uses two exponential moving averages (EMAs) to eliminate lag, as some traders view lag as a problem. The DEMA is used in a similar way to traditional moving averages (MA). The average helps confirm uptrends when the price is above the average, and helps confirm downtrends when the price is below the average. When the price crosses the average that may signal a trend change. Moving averages are also used to indicate areas of support or resistance.","id":"5e8bc014a29f2714d8b6a771","updated":"2020-04-06T23:49:40.787Z","likes":0,"shares":2324,"trendingScore":11,"usageScore":226,"sources":{"tikiDEMA.js":{"name":"tikiDEMA.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"template","module":"funCharts","caption":"Improved Footprint Imbalance Chart","indicators":[],"authorId":267823,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"0aad0f12-be02-46dd-a604-b2c403943095","text":"Used indicators: VPOC (BAR)","updated":"2021-09-16T18:20:10.906Z","likes":0,"shares":2298,"trendingScore":10,"sources":{"Improved Footprint Imbalance Chart":{"name":"Improved Footprint Imbalance Chart.template.tradovate"}},"images":[],"author":"Micheal Wesley"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Tiki QQE","entitlement":false,"authorId":1103,"indicators":["Tiki QQE"],"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"QQE is an abbreviation for the Qualitative Quantitative Estimation. The indicator is based on RSI enhanced using a smoothing technique. Unlike most indicators, Qqe has withstood the test of time regarding volatility changes, especially after the famous 2008 global financial crisis. Better still, it has no lag and rarely produces false signals.","id":"7ea2f835-8c4f-4ca1-86e0-f36b9086afb2","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2024-11-06T15:50:46.975Z","shares":2284,"trendingScore":5,"usageScore":154,"sources":{"tikiQQE.js":{"name":"tikiQQE.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"indicators":[],"caption":"VWAP AND LEVELS MOBILE","text":"Used indicators: Session High and Low for Asia, London, Pre-market Data, Initial Balance, and NYC Opening Range. Additionally, it calculates the new initial balance and midpoint for the NYC opening range session., Anchored VWAPs with various anchoring periods (yearly, monthly, weekly, daily, futures open)., p2f - Anchored VWAP, Tracks and displays up to 7 POC and 7 IB levels for market structure analysis., Tracks and displays key session levels including support, resistance, supply, demand, VAH, VAL, and more.","updated":"2025-02-16T22:56:15.276Z","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"entityType":"template","module":"funCharts","id":"dac2853d-b5bd-4665-b72b-34105c38de49","authorId":2219171,"likes":0,"usageScore":0,"shares":2281,"trendingScore":43,"sources":{"VWAP AND LEVELS MOBILE":{"name":"VWAP AND LEVELS MOBILE.template.tradovate"}},"images":["5fd5e52f-7010-44d4-8ddb-bf2a432c5eea"],"author":"servantthought"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","caption":"Initial Balance Extensions","indicators":["Initial Balance Extension"],"authorId":130646,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"70a35249-311e-4148-8666-692d7f7dea3c","text":"Tiki Opening Range indicator, but with added extensions.  Best used on the 30min timeframe.","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2021-03-17T22:06:40.190Z","likes":0,"shares":2263,"trendingScore":6,"usageScore":137,"sources":{"IB_ext.js":{"name":"IB_ext.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Seth Mo"},{"caption":"Moving Average Envelope - No Diddle (EMA,SMA,WMA,HULL)","authorId":140606,"indicators":["Moving Avg Envelope-No Diddle"],"id":"587f6806-33a6-4076-9246-f0a04706c277","text":"Draws an EMA, SMA, WMA, or Hull Envelope at a specified percentage.  Also , it allows you to color the zone between the bands.","updated":"2020-06-27T18:20:20.088Z","likes":0,"shares":2250,"trendingScore":5,"usageScore":95,"sources":{"movAvgEnvelope-NoDiddle":{"name":"movAvgEnvelope-NoDiddle.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Scott K"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Volume Delta Grid Clean","authorId":153787,"indicators":["Volume Delta Grid Clean"],"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Cleaned it up a little and renamed some of the columns to save space","id":"48a0a018-3e65-40a9-81e0-5746409b4388","updated":"2021-06-09T12:18:23.067Z","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"shares":2249,"trendingScore":10,"usageScore":109,"sources":{"VolumeDeltaGridClean.js":{"name":"VolumeDeltaGridClean.js"}},"images":[],"author":"schapes Standard"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"template","module":"funCharts","caption":"VWAP/EMA","indicators":[],"authorId":255491,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"83272973-e234-40b6-8f14-3a78e80ad8df","text":"Used indicators: VWAP, Simple Moving Average","updated":"2021-12-01T12:11:53.921Z","likes":0,"shares":2239,"trendingScore":3,"sources":{"VWAP/EMA":{"name":"VWAP/EMA.template.tradovate"}},"images":[],"author":"YEY"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"NSDT Fracking","entitlement":false,"indicators":["NSDT Fracking"],"authorId":67660,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"ec8d2394-8dcc-4896-8c2c-6bfecfc96cbc","text":"This indicator is an interesting take on the use of Fractals. It looks at recent market structure, analyzes the movement, and provides a potential Entry and Target. Because of this, you will notice that some of these trading areas are wider than others.\n\nThe Blue areas indicate a potential Long.\nThe Yellow areas indicate a potential Short.\nThe Green areas indicate a potential Long with a higher probability.\nThe Red areas indicate a potential Short with a higher probability.\n\nThere are 2 MA's available that can be changed by the trader. These will turn Green during an uptrend and Red during a downtrend for easier viewing.\n\nA suggest use of a Stop Loss is the opposite end of the candle that breaks the entry level. And when the price gets close to the target level, move your Stop to about half way through the shaded area to lock in profits in case the trade does not reach the Target and turns around.","updated":"2022-05-10T22:14:25.072Z","obfuscated":true,"likes":0,"shares":2212,"trendingScore":6,"usageScore":209,"sources":{"NSDTFracking.js":{"name":"NSDTFracking.js"}},"images":["b13f935c-25ea-42c1-a2d3-5b2376448988"],"author":"NorthStarTrading"},{"caption":"NOM Colored Price Line","authorId":137783,"indicators":["NOM Colored Price Line"],"id":"0b051adc-13af-46c8-a4b7-d45a0fc4c4ae","text":"The gray \"Last Trade Price\" line is often difficult to see on charts. This indicator allows you to use a price line with a color of your choice for better visibility. \n\nTo make this work, the \"Show Value\" option MUST BE ENABLED. It is also a good idea to check the \"Save As Default\" option to avoid having to do this every time. It works best with opacity set to 0% and with the normal \"Last Trade Price\" line disabled. \n\nNote that the line width and line style options do not have any effect on this price line. ","updated":"2020-06-30T19:13:33.459Z","likes":0,"shares":2207,"trendingScore":11,"usageScore":198,"sources":{"NOMColoredPriceLine":{"name":"NOMColoredPriceLine.js"}},"images":[],"author":"nom"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"workspace","caption":"ORDERFLOW","indicators":[],"authorId":458274,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Used modules: Chart, Trade Performance, T&S\nUsed indicators: VWAP, Volume Profiles, NOM VWAP Bands, Cumulative Delta, Previous OHLC, Tiki Opening Range\nTheme: dark","id":"ce40a6b4-cece-47b5-a829-7b592400c2c1","updated":"2024-03-12T20:58:34.417Z","likes":0,"shares":2201,"trendingScore":52,"sources":{"ORDERFLOW":{"name":"ORDERFLOW.workspace.tradovate"}},"images":[],"author":"BullGoesShort"},{"caption":"RSI in Laguerre Time Self Adjusting with Fractal Energy","authorId":132903,"indicators":["RSI in Laguerre Time SA w FE"],"id":"03aaaecc-b2b6-4206-8b7f-f63658a84032","text":"This indicator is based off Thinkorswim RSI in Laguerre Time Self adjusting with fractal energy indicator.\nSource : usethinkscript.com/threads/rsi-in-laguerre-time-self-adjusting-with-fractal-energy-usage-notes.219/","likes":0,"updated":"2020-05-25T01:52:07.295Z","shares":2201,"trendingScore":0,"usageScore":77,"sources":{"RSI_Laguerre_Time_SA_w_FE":{"name":"RSI_Laguerre_Time_SA_w_FE.js"}},"images":[],"author":"jimmyjon"},{"caption":"CVD Indicator Bottom Grid","text":"'buymeacoffee.com/sethmo'\n\nHere's how to read and interpret CVD:\n\n1. What is CVD?\n\n    Delta: For each price bar (e.g., a 5-minute candle, a daily candle), \"Delta\" is the difference between the volume of aggressive buy orders (market buys hitting limit sells) and aggressive sell orders (market sells hitting limit buys).\n        Positive Delta: More aggressive buying than selling.\n        Negative Delta: More aggressive selling than buying.\n        Zero Delta: Buying and selling pressure are equal.\n    Cumulative: CVD takes these individual \"Delta\" values and continuously adds them up over a specified period. This creates a running total, showing the overall trend of buying or selling dominance.\n\n2. How to Read CVD on a Chart:\n\nCVD is typically displayed as a separate indicator below the price chart, often as a continuous line or a histogram.\n\n    Rising CVD: Indicates that buying pressure is consistently stronger than selling pressure. This suggests bullish sentiment and confirms an uptrend.\n    Falling CVD:","updated":"2025-06-12T00:37:43.469Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"ad6ebfcf-e7d7-4a61-acda-9c67e1cebb9c","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["Volume Delta Grid Clean"],"authorId":4761649,"likes":0,"shares":2179,"trendingScore":43,"usageScore":114,"sources":{"footprintgemma.js":{"name":"footprintgemma.js"}},"images":["a85b03ed-cb0a-44e7-ba9d-4d8d2f85b4de"],"author":"SethMo"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Latter-day Trader: ATR Histogram","indicators":["LDT - ATR Histogram"],"authorId":207522,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"94476dd2-dd06-450c-be5b-ae7696194390","text":"Displays the Average True Range (ATR) as a histogram.","updated":"2021-05-05T03:36:53.028Z","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"trendingScore":16,"shares":2171,"usageScore":264,"sources":{"LDT_ATR_Histogram.js":{"name":"LDT_ATR_Histogram.js"}},"images":[],"author":"LatterDayTrader"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"supply&Demand","entitlement":false,"indicators":["SMA"],"authorId":1099401,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"This Text is too short","id":"cea5db88-4c0b-407b-9640-7f5f6f764247","updated":"2024-05-19T04:26:06.795Z","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"usageScore":46,"shares":2167,"trendingScore":12,"sources":{"SuppDemandZones.js":{"name":"SuppDemandZones.js"},"SupplyandDemand.js":{"name":"SupplyandDemand.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Lookitsmikey"},{"caption":"NukeGuy - Order Blocks","text":"Plots true Order Blocks on the current chart timeframe using close-based BOS (no wick breaks) and body-only OB zones. Includes a mitigation mode toggle (First Touch vs 50% / CE) with optional hiding of mitigated/invalidated blocks. Clean, fast, and built for ICT / SMC execution with a configurable lookback (days) and max blocks for clutter control.","updated":"2026-02-21T00:52:14.944Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"7d36a374-6e09-4c18-9e5e-08ab58f843a0","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["NukeGuy - Order Blocks"],"authorId":6759560,"likes":0,"shares":2154,"trendingScore":321,"usageScore":3221,"sources":{"NukeBLOCKS.js":{"name":"NukeBLOCKS.js"}},"images":["f3077b31-d5c7-4ebb-ab8e-c7e711ddc78c"],"author":"NukeGuy"},{"caption":"Cumulative Delta Heatmap","text":"A cumulative delta heatmap, twiddle with the params to get the best results for your setup","updated":"2025-08-08T09:16:14.868Z","link":"https://community.tradovate.com/c/custom-indicators","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"e4e8c871-1cc0-44e4-87f6-b7e1facf0781","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["heatmap"],"authorId":3269993,"likes":0,"trendingScore":110,"usageScore":244,"shares":2143,"sources":{"new-heatmap.js":{"name":"new-heatma