l line can be applied to look for signal line crossovers. A directional bias can be determined with the absolute level. Bullish and bearish divergences can be used to anticipate reversals.","id":"5a6de9793b9ee600019c0e9e","updated":"2018-09-24T13:18:03.301Z","likes":0,"shares":1989,"trendingScore":7,"usageScore":59,"sources":{"tikiTRIX.js":{"name":"tikiTRIX.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"colorScheme","module":"funCharts","caption":"DK1_Sethmo","indicators":[],"authorId":130646,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Derived from dark color scheme. Easier on the eyes. Same background color as FB dark mode.\n\nBackground: black. Labels: white. Crosshair annotations: darkgray. Grid lines: black. High price: limegreen. Low price: crimson. Last price: darksalmon. Daily profile: darkslategray. Buy orders: limegreen. Sell orders: crimson.","id":"0ebcff58-00f8-4170-b123-67f7d8c7c28f","updated":"2021-06-10T16:14:30.802Z","likes":0,"shares":1981,"trendingScore":30,"sources":{"DK1_Sethmo":{"name":"DK1_Sethmo.colorScheme.tradovate"}},"images":[],"author":"Seth Mo"},{"caption":"p2f - Chande Kroll Stop","authorId":138571,"indicators":["p2f - Chande Kroll Stop"],"id":"3105dc3c-54d8-4afc-9232-a59088ed3d07","text":"Chande Kroll Stop is a trend-following indicator that identifies the stop loss for a long or short position by using a variation on directional movement. It is calculated on the average true range of an instrument's volatility.","likes":0,"updated":"2020-06-21T20:29:43.723Z","shares":1970,"trendingScore":0,"usageScore":56,"sources":{"p2f-chandeKrollStop":{"name":"p2f-chandeKrollStop.js"}},"images":[],"author":"paidtofade"},{"caption":"Fractal Energy","authorId":105135,"indicators":["Fractal Energy"],"id":"27471aad-bcb6-40a4-b189-442c3bab5c38","text":"Fractal Energy shows the energy and with the levels within this indicator you can detect powerful energy levels followed by an expansion - whatever direction (it's the Gamma of the Laguarde RSI).","updated":"2020-06-07T20:02:49.765Z","likes":0,"shares":1964,"trendingScore":13,"usageScore":34,"sources":{"fractalenergy_done":{"name":"fractalenergy_done.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tradalex"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Footprint by Hector , Credits to sethmo for code base","entitlement":false,"indicators":["Footprint"],"authorId":1103907,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Footprint by hector","id":"54dc1eda-35ec-4f49-b48f-3152e1860615","updated":"2024-04-01T14:13:19.630Z","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"trendingScore":24,"usageScore":79,"shares":1955,"sources":{"footprint.js":{"name":"footprint.js"}},"images":["bb73ac7c-6561-4c19-b47f-1ad3b5c5ba7d"],"author":"Hector"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"https://community.tradovate.com/c/custom-indicators/6","caption":"RexDog Average (RDA) with ATR Bands","entitlement":false,"authorId":211205,"indicators":["Rexdog Average ATR"],"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"This indicator includes the RexDog average but provides you with the ability to plot (and customize) both above and below ATR-calculated bands.\n\nHow This Works\n\nJust as with the RexDog Average we take the 6 ATR data points (200, 100, 50, 24, 9, 5). We then create an average by dividing by 6.\n\nUsage:\nPrice above the RexDog AVG = long momentum bias\nPrice below the RexDog AVG = short momentum bias\nWith the ATR addition most likely your usage will be similar to Bollinger Bands . While not the same as in deviations much of the same principles might apply, especially with customization.\n\n*Note: we have banned the word “trend” in the RexDog Trading System\n\nAdditional Usage Advice:\n\nIf price rips through the average your momentum bias should probably change. 80% of the time when price moves through the RexDog Average it will come back and test the area around average within 1-2 bars. 20% of the time it does not. The momentum is so strong in that direction so look for a 50-70% tests of the bar that impulse through.","id":"9155fb91-cc5b-44c6-81eb-4cff1c85c87a","updated":"2023-01-04T19:16:39.888Z","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"trendingScore":1,"shares":1944,"usageScore":324,"sources":{"rexDogAverageATR.js":{"name":"rexDogAverageATR.js"}},"images":["f8673def-8ecc-4149-bc45-49742f258400","fe76fd48-c853-45c5-b10e-a3ad95c4fc33"],"author":"RexDogTrading"},{"caption":"Moving Avg WonderCloud (3 period)","authorId":140606,"indicators":["Moving Avg WonderCloud - 3 period"],"id":"61c42694-a32e-4e9e-ac06-bf3ff662f04e","text":"Draws and colors a cloud based on 3 moving average periods.  You can select SMA, EMA, Hull, Weighted and Modified for moving averages.","likes":0,"updated":"2020-07-29T21:02:41.569Z","shares":1915,"trendingScore":3,"usageScore":222,"sources":{"HMA":{"name":"HMA.js"},"movAvg_WonderCloud_3period":{"name":"movAvg_WonderCloud_3period.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Scott K"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"template","module":"funCharts","caption":"Sethmo TPO","indicators":[],"authorId":234569,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Basic TPO template setup to split Globex and RTH sessions","id":"27d91ef0-2923-48a1-93ec-3e84aeb6be63","updated":"2021-06-07T14:35:11.245Z","likes":0,"shares":1907,"trendingScore":11,"sources":{"Sethmo TPO":{"name":"Sethmo TPO.template.tradovate"}},"images":[],"author":"sethm"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"template","module":"funCharts","caption":"Cumulative Delta","indicators":[],"authorId":2383465,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Used indicators: Cumulative Delta, NOM VWAP Bands, Volume Profiles, VWAP","id":"a2ddae9c-ba1a-4c7b-b1b1-785c7d4ce6b0","updated":"2024-05-20T08:55:25.150Z","likes":0,"shares":1905,"trendingScore":29,"sources":{"Cumulative Delta":{"name":"Cumulative Delta.template.tradovate"}},"images":[],"author":"Mohammed Amer"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Latter-day Trader: Leg Counter (beta)","authorId":207522,"indicators":["LDT - Leg Counter"],"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Counts legs based on simple rules. An up leg continues when a higher low is made. A down leg continues when a lower high is made. \n\nIt defaults to show the leg count on the signal bar. If you wish to make it look more like the leg count in byebyemoney's Two-legged Pullback indicator, you can enable the option to show it on the entry bar.\n\nIf you find this useful, please consider tipping me at buymeacoffee.com/latterdaytrader.","id":"ba60848e-cd42-48db-ad6f-d03c075d7131","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2021-07-10T05:44:49.250Z","likes":0,"shares":1893,"trendingScore":2,"usageScore":104,"sources":{"LDT_Leg_Counter.js":{"name":"LDT_Leg_Counter.js"}},"images":[],"author":"LatterDayTrader"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"workspace","caption":"Sethmo NQ","indicators":[],"authorId":139961,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Used modules: Chart, Positions, Quote Board\nUsed indicators: LDT - Moving Average Bands, Cumulative Delta, RSI IN LAGUERRE TIME SA W FE, VWAP, LDT - Colorful MA WonderCloud, Sethmo Initial Balance Extension, LDT - ThreeTen Oscillator, Tiki Bollinger Bands v2, Std. Dev Volatility, Moving Average - w/Trend Color, p2f - Adaptive Moving Average, Volume Profiles, LDT - VWAP Bands, Sethmo p2f - Dead Simple Reversal, LDT - Colorful KAMA WonderCloud, LDT - Multi-Colored MACD Histogram, p2f - Overlay Range Boxes (LDT), LDT - Colorful MA WonderCloud (v2), Exponential Moving Average, LDT - Williams Fractals, Parabolic SAR, Sethmo CCI + EMA, tystr - Improved Tiki Trend\nTheme: dark","id":"0ae1b523-bad9-423e-9fe5-70c0d4999667","updated":"2021-06-03T21:17:21.726Z","likes":0,"shares":1886,"trendingScore":5,"sources":{"Sethmo NQ":{"name":"Sethmo NQ.workspace.tradovate"}},"images":[],"author":"sethmo"},{"caption":"ICTWHOLEpackage","text":"IFVG Blocks Session and KZ Highs and lows","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"47d02555-833a-4cbc-9c65-9e25467e1bab","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement"