:1103,"indicators":["Tiki Wilder's Smooth Average"],"text":"Wilder’s Smoothing (WS-MA) was developed buy J. Welles Wilder, Jr. and first presented in his landmark book New Concepts in Technical Trading Systems (June 1978).  He used it as a component in several of his other indicators including the RSI which is one of the most popular technical indicators of all time.","id":"5d1b7a9ce582c57cc86c0430","updated":"2019-07-02T15:39:08.202Z","likes":0,"shares":1689,"trendingScore":3,"usageScore":118,"sources":{"tikiWSMA.js":{"name":"tikiWSMA.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Risk/Reward Drawing Tool","entitlement":false,"indicators":["Win/Loss PositionV3"],"authorId":218261,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"A modified version of Position Drawing Tool by ALENNERT.\n\nThis version is heavily modified to my personal preferences. This does not have tooltips, so hovering over the drawing and pressing SHIFT will not show any data, instead you can toggle visibility of select information in settings menu of the drawing.\n\nLike the original version risk to reward can only be changed in settings menu. Unlike the original version drawing the risk to reward is more natural in my opinion.","id":"ba77c13b-eaa3-46e4-8567-cdc8299b4d52","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2024-04-30T11:57:19.478Z","shares":1681,"trendingScore":-1,"sources":{"winloss.js":{"name":"winloss.js"}},"images":[],"author":"dartrader"},{"caption":"On Balance Volume","authorId":87472,"indicators":["On Balance Volume"],"id":"cea62229-0866-4306-82fe-c5eabaa3249a","text":"On Balance Volume keeps a running total of volume flowing into or out of a security. When the security closes higher than the previous close, all of the day's volume is considered up-volume. A close lower than the previous day's results in all of the day's volume considered down-volume. A rising OBV is defined as a sign of smart money flowing into a security. As the public then moves into the security, both the security and the OBV will surge ahead. If the price movement precedes the OBV movement, it is called a \"non-confirmation.\" Non-confirmations tend to occur at bull market tops or at bear market bottoms.\n\nWhen the security's price closes up, the day's OBV is created by adding the day's volume to the cumulative total. The day's volume is subtracted from the cumulative total when the price closes down.","updated":"2020-07-23T23:13:13.880Z","likes":0,"shares":1680,"trendingScore":6,"usageScore":110,"sources":{"onBalanceVolume":{"name":"onBalanceVolume.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Sanjay Dubey"},{"caption":"True Momentum Oscillator","authorId":87472,"indicators":["TMO (True Momentum Oscillator)"],"id":"4d01ac41-b393-4c1a-9c6e-4eafb897ec31","text":"TMO (True Momentum Oscillator)","updated":"2020-09-28T02:43:21.258Z","likes":0,"shares":1673,"trendingScore":4,"usageScore":216,"sources":{"tmo":{"name":"tmo.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Sanjay Dubey"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Latter-day Trader: Stochastic MACD","indicators":["LDT - Stochastic MACD"],"authorId":207522,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"cc80ec1f-8b9b-4b07-ab6d-55163166a416","text":"It is part MACD and part Stochastics. The logic was copied from the ThinkOrSwim indicator with the same name, so please see the link below for more information. \n\nhttps :// tlc.thinkorswim.com/center/reference/Tech-Indicators/studies-library/R-S/StochasticMACD","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2021-05-30T14:17:14.070Z","likes":0,"shares":1671,"trendingScore":8,"usageScore":117,"sources":{"LDT_Stochastic_MACD.js":{"name":"LDT_Stochastic_MACD.js"}},"images":[],"author":"LatterDayTrader"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Sethmo Horizontal Line Tool w/Text","entitlement":false,"authorId":130646,"indicators":["+ Horizontal Line w/Text"],"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Horizontal line drawing tool with ability to attach text to the line. Text is limited to a pre-defined list. can edit the list in code explorer.\n\nText is tied to the second anchor point. If anyone can figure out how to statically draw text on the right side of the chart, that would be ideal.\n\n/Sethmo out.","id":"114100b4-153b-45cd-8c92-8e29b1e00b00","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2022-03-09T23:40:42.400Z","trendingScore":22,"shares":1655,"sources":{"betterLines.js":{"name":"betterLines.js"}},"images":["5906c753-6cee-4762-956f-c7f552eaae37","70681b51-51d3-45f8-b605-af7dfb0ed805"],"author":"Seth Mo"},{"caption":"Beta - OGC Hull Trend ","indicators":["OGC Hull Trend"],"authorId":86160,"text":"A much needed and often requested feature on the a classic indicator. This Hull Moving Average includes a plot when the previous value is less than the current value and a color change  function to assist with trend changes. ","id":"9d17b686-ed06-4413-9cf1-05fa5f4796e2","updated":"2020-05-07T15:50:37.299Z","likes":0,"shares":1643,"trendingScore":-12,"usageScore":39,"sources":{"OGCHull":{"name":"OGCHull.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Onegreencandle"},{"caption":"Smart Money Concepts (Advanced)","text":"Smart Money Concepts (Advanced)","updated":"2025-01-10T16:44:37.533Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"e917eabf-66fa-4cf2-a884-96f8677900ad","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["SMA"],"authorId":3074421,"likes":0,"shares":1642,"trendingScore":38,"usageScore":71,"sources":{"smcadv.js":{"name":"smcadv.js"}},"images":[],"author":"fhpc"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"template","module":"funCharts","caption":"TBM","indicators":[],"authorId":336413,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Used indicators: Cumulative Delta, VWAP, p2f - Adaptive Moving Average, Volume Profiles","id":"dff5a9dd-4ad2-4db7-99f5-bfe9cf2c8b42","updated":"2022-02-17T00:17:10.092Z","likes":0,"shares":1638,"trendingScore":4,"sources":{"TBM":{"name":"TBM.template.tradovate"}},"images":[],"author":"dar"},{"caption":"Keltner Channels - No Diddle Zone","authorId":140606,"indicators":["Keltner Channels - No Diddle"],"text":"Keltner Channels based on SMA, EMA, WMA, Hull with optionable shading","id":"9e65d263-5ef7-495b-8f1f-bdd8ed756ac4","likes":0,"updated":"2020-07-09T20:10:45.851Z","trendingScore":7,"shares":1633,"usageScore":129,"sources":{"HMA":{"name":"HMA.js"},"keltnerChannels-NoDiddle":{"name":"keltnerChannels-NoDiddle.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Scott K"},{"caption":"Risk To Reward Tool With Contract Sizing","text":"RR_TOOL_4C is a flexible Risk To Reward drawing tool modeled after TradingView’s Long/Short Position tools. It uses a simple 3-click process: set the entry, stop loss, and profit target levels.\nThe tool calculates position sizing based on account size, tick value, and risk % per trade. The reward level is fully adjustable, and key stats like R/R ratio and contract quantity are displayed in real time.\n\nTip: This tool uses saved default settings. After refreshing or restarting the platform, re-enter your risk settings and click “Save as Default” to retain them for future drawings.\n\nOnce installed, you will find RR_TOOL_4C in the Drawing Tools menu.","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"c91579cd-97ec-47c2-9aa9-06bc6fc6b2aa","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["RR_TOOL_4C"],"authorId":172419,"likes":0,"usageScore":0,"updated":"2026-03-17T03:01:27.436Z","shares":1623,"trendingScore":45,"sources":{"RR_TOOL_4C.js":{"name":"RR_TOOL_4C.js"}},"images":["37e00b2e-6bbe-4758-b086-9062e8c497e1","adb182ed-03f6-40dc-a8b2-0fa00b073aef"],"author":"FourC"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Commodity Channel Index Trigger","entitlement":false,"indicators":["Commodity Channel Index Trigger"],"authorId":226906,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"CCI Trigger is a simple tool which plots the \"buy\" or \"sell\" trigger overlayed on the main chart. It uses the \"CCI key\" value as the overbought or oversold. For example in the current market trend if CCI is above 200, it's an overbought condition so the indicator will plot a down arrow, and so forth.","id":"2a2d873e-32f2-47ab-9810-1c4df911f769","updated":"2023-06-15T22:50:48.169Z","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"shares":1602,"trendingScore":8,"usageScore":74,"sources":{"cciTrigger.js":{"name":"cciTrigger.js"}},"images":["708e46ee-9652-4d85-b310-65f9d1898baa","b722c086-76a6-4564-bc7d-0b3ad5bf5a9d"],"author":"CaliTrader"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Latter-day Trader: Multi-Timeframe Moving Average (v1)","indicators":["LDT - Multi-Timeframe Moving Average"],"authorId":207522,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Display moving averages from a couple higher timeframes (MINUTE charts only). Make sure your HTF Period values are higher than the current chart's timeframe. So if you are on the 1 minute chart, HTFPeriod1 should be greater than 1. Also, the HTF Periods should be a multiple of the current timeframe. If you are on the 2 minute chart, you should not set HTF Period to 5, etc. \n\nI will assume you are smart enough to do the math and I don't claim that indicator will work with all settings. Make sure you compare with a similar indicator on a different platform before relying on it for your live trades.","id":"d6a606c4-fc21-4fd2-b370-c94c11fd6081","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2021-04-17T20:05:54.707Z","likes":0,"shares":1598,"trendingScore":9,"usageScore":270,"sources":{"LDT_MTF_MA.js":{"name":"LDT_MTF_MA.js"}},"images":[],"author":"LatterDayTrader"},{"caption":"ALNY Session Highs & Lows","text":"Asia, London, & New York Session Highs & Lows\n\nAlso has a Daily Mode for marking daily OHLC levels\nExcellent touch detection for when levels get hit\nHas 3 different touch rules: Wick Touch, Close Through, Full Body Overlap","link":"https://community.tradovate.com/t/a-l-n-y-highs-lows/12550?u=unlimitidities","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"02b2f68d-aec9-47da-a7c1-af54da67f982","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["ALNY Highs N Lows"],"authorId":5094514,"likes":0,"updated":"2026-03-10T02:23:14.550Z","trendingScore":240,"usageScore":1334,"shares":1590,"sources":{"SessionHighLows.js":{"name":"SessionHighLows.js"}},"images":["1b0285fa-d2ab-44ba-92a7-b31f552b2ab0","58219018-bf5b-4680-8baa-2395bc6eedc2","880b719a-7756-456a-bbbb-37ec0a4e19cb"],"author":"Unlimitidities"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"MACD","entitlement":false,"indicators":["MACD with Multi Color Histogram"],"authorId":2447526,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"MACD","id":"ba6be1b9-7064-4e47-ac1a-a2dc12203120","updated":"2024-04-08T01:19:05.091Z","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"trendingScore":11,"usageScore":99,"shares":1567,"sources":{"MACD_ColorHistogram.js":{"name":"MACD_ColorHistogram.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Pnguyen"},{"caption":"Tiki DeMarker","indicators":["Tiki DeMarker"],"authorId":1103,"text":"The DeMarker indicator (also known as simply DeM) is an oscillator that derives its values by comparing the maximum and minimum prices achieved in the current time period with the equivalent prices achieved in the previous period. From this comparison, the indicator attempts to assess the directional bias of the market. At the same time, it indicates overbought and oversold conditions, and from these, attempts to identify points of trend exhaustion.","id":"5b90816cd67bd10d04d8d0a9","updated":"2018-09-24T13:17:18.809Z","likes":0,"shares":1567,"trendingScore":-2,"usageScore":75,"sources":{"tikiDeMarker.js":{"name":"tikiDeMarker.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"caption":"Tiki Price Momentum Oscillator (PMO)","authorId":1103,"indicators":["Tiki PMO"],"text":"The DecisionPoint Price Momentum Oscillator (PMO) is an oscillator based on a Rate of Change (ROC) calculation that is smoothed twice with exponential moving averages that use a custom smoothing process. Because the PMO is normalized, it can also be used as a relative strength tool. Stocks can thus be ranked by their PMO value as an expression of relative strength.","id":"5a20d09cdd1dbc000194e4fb","updated":"2018-09-24T13:17:44.693Z","likes":0,"shares":1563,"trendingScore":-2,"usageScore":20,"sources":{"tikiPMO.js":{"name":"tikiPMO.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"caption":"p2f - Scale Zones","authorId":138571,"indicators":["p2f - Scale Zones"],"text":"Provides a simple method for marking zones of relative extremes according to the last close. Note the center of the zones can be overriden. Inspired by the TOS indicator from Gary Markoski of the same name.","id":"061ca3ec-ad15-46da-a27a-d1473fbfabc9","likes":0,"updated":"2020-06-30T03:50:54.939Z","shares":1520,"trendingScore":1,"usageScore":10,"sources":{"p2f-scaleZones":{"name":"p2f-scaleZones.js"}},"images":[],"author":"paidtofade"},{"caption":"Volume Profile, colored by Volume Zone Oscillator","text":"This rolling Volume Profile includes Point of Control, Value area boundaries. The volume aggregation time can be adjusted in minute increments, a 240 (4h) value seems a good choice for a 1 min chart. The profile is colored by the average the price of the volume spend in the respective Volume Zone oscillator zone (grey for +/- 5%, indecision zone) red for -5 to -40 %, dark red < -40% and green for 5 to 40 %, dar green for > 40 %","updated":"2026-04-02T07:50:34.627Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"3c1b1d07-6b0e-447e-b9a3-63c053357e87","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["Volume Zone Oscillator - Customizable Profile Variant"],"authorId":707636,"likes":0,"shares":1517,"trendingScore":288,"usageScore":971,"sources":{"VZOProfile.js":{"name":"VZOProfile.js"}},"images":["2b0360b5-4358-4a31-90e8-6b33f58c0ba0","da98c44d-ca08-4014-b5a5-4f9ab96ca776"],"author":"TradeEscape"},{"caption":"BMCTrendChannel","indicators":["Trend Line & Chan