idden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Gann Lines","authorId":72977,"indicators":["GannLines"],"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"cd7ebaaf-f8a8-49b6-89bc-6c235ac990ef","text":"Gann Lines form W.D. Gann. Theory centers around the square of 9 and plays heavily into the idea of harmonics. This will rotate based on the .125 degrees from the main square labeled \"midline\". Hope you enjoy.","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2021-04-13T22:42:24.753Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":10,"shares":1390,"usageScore":105,"sources":{"GannLines.js":{"name":"GannLines.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Proshot"},{"caption":"Tiki Ticks","indicators":["Tiki Ticks"],"authorId":1103,"text":"This indicator is similar to a standard volume histogram, but instead uses trades per bar (ticks).","id":"5e7a36d19cbb3c9a914b3f93","updated":"2020-03-24T16:35:29.149Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":3,"shares":1381,"usageScore":59,"sources":{"tikiTicks.js":{"name":"tikiTicks.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Latter-day Trader: Volume Delta Grid Extension","indicators":["LDT - Volume Delta Grid Extension"],"authorId":207522,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"d83c05b9-fb2a-45a5-b6ef-333ef6aa25e6","text":"As requested on a Discord group...this builds on the original Volume Delta Grid and displays two additional rows: Bar Delta Low and Bar Delta High. (You will still need the original indicator. I would recommend adding this extension first and then the original. That way, the bar low, bar high, and current/final bar deltas are closest to each other.)\n\nThese two new rows are just the highest and lowest values for the bar. When combined with the current/final delta value, you can gauge the range and the direction of the delta within the bar.\n\nFor bars that are in the past (at the time the chart loads), the bar delta low and bar delta high will be the same values as the final delta value for the bar.","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2021-05-21T04:34:58.439Z","likes":0,"usageScore":18,"shares":1379,"trendingScore":4,"sources":{"LDT_VolumeDeltaGrid_Modified.js":{"name":"LDT_VolumeDeltaGrid_Modified.js"}},"images":[],"author":"LatterDayTrader"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Delta Target V5","authorId":140399,"indicators":["Delta Target V5"],"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"3c6cadeb-cb17-41da-95c6-287c376cdb97","text":"Using delta trend to also filter entries. Now you can adjust the number of contracts if the number goes to high. If it goes above the default 400 no buy signal will be triggered, only triggers above set number of contracts and below 400. No visualization, you need to use deltatrend also if you want to see the trend dot.","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2021-04-19T08:00:32.291Z","likes":0,"trendingScore":14,"shares":1358,"usageScore":52,"sources":{"DeltaTarget_V5.js":{"name":"DeltaTarget_V5.js"}},"images":[],"author":"DragonPT"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Latter-day Trader: Colorful MA WonderCloud","authorId":207522,"indicators":["LDT - Colorful MA WonderCloud"],"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"4211f113-df50-4f34-a9bc-3fbe6cc58f40","text":"Modified from the original WonderCloud. You can now define four colors instead of two for the cloud itself. This allows you to quickly see if the up or down trend is getting weaker or gaining strength.","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2021-05-20T13:39:44.735Z","shares":1353,"trendingScore":3,"usageScore":80,"sources":{"LDT_Colorful_WonderCloud.js":{"name":"LDT_Colorful_WonderCloud.js"}},"images":[],"author":"LatterDayTrader"},{"caption":"VWAP STDEV","text":"Wvap avec 3 standard déviation","updated":"2025-02-25T17:59:58.680Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"a158dfa7-3ac9-45e2-a532-c825eb32b98f","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["VWAP Stdev"],"authorId":4319067,"likes":0,"shares":1350,"trendingScore":37,"usageScore":550,"sources":{"vwapstdev.js":{"name":"vwapstdev.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Lemilya"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Measure bars and ticks","entitlement":false,"indicators":["Measure Bars and Ticks"],"authorId":2638059,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Allows you to measure the vertical and horizontal distances between two selected points on a candlestick chart by bars and ticks. This provides the number of points, the equivalent tick count, and the bar count between the selected points. With a clear and configurable display, traders can see a line connecting the two points and the calculated distances shown with an adjustable offset to ensure the text is visible and unobstructed. This tool is helpful for those who need precise distance measurements to make informed trading decisions.","id":"01a0762e-9124-42d0-afe7-663cb459080f","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2024-06-14T19:19:27.386Z","shares":1335,"trendingScore":10,"sources":{"MeasureBarTicks.js":{"name":"MeasureBarTicks.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Swift"},{"caption":"MACD SMA","authorId":174571,"text":"MACD calculated with SMA","id":"4c69d34d-67cf-4a2f-98c7-e2a2c3579686","likes":0,"indicators":["MACD SMA"],"updated":"2020-12-01T04:05:23.895Z","shares":1326,"trendingScore":0,"usageScore":10,"sources":{"MACDSMA":{"name":"MACDSMA.js"}},"images":[],"author":"LTC"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"template","module":"funCharts","caption":"Footprint","indicators":[],"authorId":267823,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Footprint by zed","id":"0df1a5a6-ce0e-42ef-83af-aa6ee1b6d262","updated":"2021-09-15T20:30:10.019Z","likes":0,"shares":1321,"trendingScore":5,"sources":{"Footprint":{"name":"Footprint.template.tradovate"}},"images":[],"author":"Micheal Wesley"},{"caption":"Tiki Range Forecast","indicators":["Tiki Range Forecast"],"authorId":1103,"text":"This indicator is designed for the `range` and `range momentum` charts, and will plot an upper and lower range boundary based on the remaining range of the current bar. ","id":"5b60a16135e8ae00013cc523","updated":"2018-09-24T13:17:47.800Z","likes":0,"shares":1317,"trendingScore":-2,"usageScore":47,"sources":{"tikiRangeForecast":{"name":"tikiRangeForecast.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Aggressive Candles","entitlement":false,"indicators":["LDT - Aggressive Candles (b02)"],"authorId":201554,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Gives you an easy way to identify which side is in control on any particular candle.  Also, makes your chart look hella cool. \n\nRemember use responsibly and death to all nihilists!","id":"6162e3b2-e905-4e60-89fd-938ec08b52ca","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2023-01-31T13:22:35.733Z","likes":0,"shares":1311,"trendingScore":5,"usageScore":171,"sources":{"LDT_Aggressive_Candles_b02.js":{"name":"LDT_Aggressive_Candles_b02.js"}},"images":[],"author":"DudeMan"},{"caption":"On Balance Volume Modified","authorId":87472,"indicators":["On Balance Volume Modified"],"id":"5febcdff-0a02-44de-af66-845fbcb6ac25","text":"The OnBalanceVolumeModified (OBVM) study is a technical indicator introduced by Vitali Apirine. It is a variation of OnBalanceVolume (OBV). In the modified version, OBV is given a smoothing (by an exponential moving average, by default). In addition, a signal line is introduced. The signal line is a slower moving average of the smoothed-out OBV.  \n\nWhen the main line of the OBVM is rising, the volume might be gaining positive pressure, which may further result in an increase of the price. Conversely, decreasing OBVM may signify decreasing volume pressure and a further price reduction. \n\nThe main line can also be analyzed in terms of divergences from the main price plot. The signal line can be used to identify crossovers.","updated":"2020-07-23T23:15:08.429Z","likes":0,"shares":1300,"trendingScore":3,"usageScore":15,"sources":{"onBalanceVolumeModified":{"name":"onBalanceVolumeModified.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Sanjay Dubey"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"https://community.tradovate.com/t/new-strongbars-indicator/9166","caption":"StrongBars","entitlement":false,"indicators":["StrongBars"],"authorId":753811,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Highlight candles that are above a threshold of their average volume, delta, or range, or any combination of those conditions.\n\nLookback period: how many bars back to determine the average value.\nProximity to average: the threshold for highlighting bars (if 1, bars will be colored if current value is above 1x the average, etc).\n\nIf all three filters are on, bars will be highlighted if they are above average volume, delta, and range, making them very strong bars.","id":"90dc1db4-7035-4e65-bf77-3c0f7098da61","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2024-04-06T14:24:21.326Z","shares":1281,"trendingScore":26,"usageScore":75,"sources":{"StrongBars":{"name":"StrongBars"}},"images":["bfbf7c7e-2102-4fd3-a5fc-8adb4c7ca871","c45603ef-450f-45f8-b5b8-2c3591c97c2a","d68daaf7-e31a-4549-b38c-1bcc76ebd53a"],"author":"ekb"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"https://community.tradovate.com/t/indicator-conversion-from-tradingview-pinescript/4811/5?u=tikidave","caption":"Tiki RSI Bands","entitlement":false,"authorId":1103,"indicators":["Tiki RSI Bands"],"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"This indicator takes the RSI values and converts the 70, 50, and 30 levels as price levels forming support and resistance bands.","id":"46abcb9c-bfb5-4f35-9e32-a1b535ffc386","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2024-11-06T15:51:53.611Z","shares":1279,"trendingScore":6,"usageScore":66,"sources":{"tikiRSIBands.js":{"name":"tikiRSIBands.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Tiki Dave"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"template","module":"funCharts","caption":"tpo footprint","indicators":[],"authorId":334433,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"tpo footprint","id":"66305987-a5c4-4c80-935b-0ca94a7f