fade"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Spike Delta Volume","entitlement":false,"indicators":["Nic SpikeVolume"],"authorId":960081,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Shows bid/ask delta volume with yellow spikes for absorption.","id":"9b210cab-e144-4cc9-9ce8-d655a880bebd","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"updated":"2023-12-29T03:43:53.813Z","shares":1107,"trendingScore":18,"usageScore":131,"sources":{"NIC_SpikeVolume.js":{"name":"NIC_SpikeVolume.js"}},"images":["36405fc6-99b1-4195-a27b-6fc7a889189d"],"author":"NicTheMajestic"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Eman One Minute Algo Run (OMAR)","entitlement":false,"indicators":["Eman One Minute Algo Run (OMAR)"],"authorId":574029,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"This is the range for the one minute candle with labels","id":"a9ca5e09-b1ec-49bf-8edc-8dcfe34eb830","updated":"2023-07-31T19:48:01.405Z","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"shares":1105,"trendingScore":10,"usageScore":60,"sources":{"emanOMAR.js":{"name":"emanOMAR.js"}},"images":["1e8d7196-83b3-477b-8b0d-e2abe79e3613","71f0dad7-ecd7-4412-8b12-7dd5063facc7"],"author":"emansenpai"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Squeeze Dots Overlay v1","authorId":187183,"indicators":["Squeeze Dots Overlay v1"],"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"7f068791-6033-4837-91ac-675f93b4983a","text":"This indicator is based on the Community Indicator: \"Tiki Squeeze\".\n\nThis modification removes the momentum histogram and only 'plots the dots'. Meant to be as an overlay on other momentum oscillators.\n\n\nFrom the original description:\nThe Squeeze indicator attempts to identify periods of consolidation in a market. In general, the market is either in a period of quiet consolidation or vertical price discovery. Once a market enters into a \"squeeze\", we watch the overall momentum to help forecast the market direction and await a release of market energy. The red and green dots along the zero line indicate if there is a squeeze or not. A red dot means there is a squeeze condition in effect. A green dot means that we are not currently in a squeeze. The first green dot after one or more red dots is where the squeeze is said to have \"fired\".\n\nThank you to Tiki Dave for writing the code.","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2021-06-05T16:20:29.858Z","likes":0,"shares":1103,"trendingScore":1,"usageScore":13,"sources":{"bnotb_Squeeze_Dots_Overlay_v1.js":{"name":"bnotb_Squeeze_Dots_Overlay_v1.js"}},"images":["b51f2da6-a84c-44b7-abb9-aee8f807d19e"],"author":"bnotb"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Latter-day Trader: Magnum's 3/6/9/12 Rotation Levels","entitlement":false,"authorId":207522,"indicators":["LDT - Magnum's 3/6/9/12 Levels"],"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"d679173a-fea5-4fee-b532-3b43b5faa71a","text":"If you find this or any of my indicators useful, please consider sending me a tip: buymeacoffee.com/latterdaytrader\n\nNaming is hard. Based on the work of Magnum, this indicator will look at certain start times of the trading day and draw a box around the body of the candle that has the highest volume for a given duration from the start time. \n\nThis does not work on Legacy charts. And it has been designed with the 1 minute chart in mind. It may work with other time frames.","obfuscated":false,"updated":"2021-10-13T15:16:01.719Z","likes":0,"shares":1092,"trendingScore":2,"usageScore":50,"sources":{"LDT_Magnums_369_Levels.js":{"name":"LDT_Magnums_369_Levels.js"}},"images":[],"author":"LatterDayTrader"},{"caption":"NCK CVD Histogram V27 - Cumulative Volume Delta Divs, Caps, Exh","text":"What this does:\n CVD Histogram that flags divergences using a 3-stage logic:\n 1) BAR test (current bar vs previous bar)\n 2) WINDOW test (current bar vs N bars ago using LookBack)\n 3) Optional SWING-EXTREME ASSIST (if both fail): compare to the most extreme price inside window.\n\nV26  Changes:\n• Session time is toggled via `continuous24hSession`.\n        When OFF (RTH), CVD accumulator resets at each RTH open \n\n *  Patch A: If you change 24h↔RTH at runtime, the indicator hard-resets its internal accumulators and windows. If carryAdaptiveFloorAcrossSessions is OFF, adaptive buffers are cleared too and will reseed as needed.\n\n* Patch B: On each RTH open we reset session accumulators/window refs. If carryAdaptiveFloorAcrossSessions is OFF, adaptive buffers are cleared and seeding flags reset. If ON, we keep\nadaptive buffers (regime continuity).\n \n * Patch C When carryAdaptiveFloorAcrossSessions is ON, we trim adaptive buffers to adaptiveWindow length on each RTH open","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"12cdf8a9-5f87-464d-a96f-7659c4a661df","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["NCK CVD v27 — Hybrid Adaptive Floor"],"authorId":132498,"likes":0,"updated":"2026-05-12T14:23:44.710Z","shares":1088,"trendingScore":34,"usageScore":219,"sources":{"CVD_Divergence_NCK.js":{"name":"CVD_Divergence_NCK.js"}},"images":[],"author":"NorCalKyle"},{"caption":"Precision Trader Bot","text":"This tools  include multiple indicators (SMA, EMA, MACD, RSI, volume, ATR) along with a volatility filter and confirmed breakout signals along with buy and sell signals to give you insight and accuracy while trading","updated":"2025-02-25T19:44:24.113Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"368e2efb-4fc3-44ae-9912-a7bad4e89386","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["SMA"],"authorId":4311093,"likes":0,"shares":1040,"trendingScore":13,"usageScore":55,"sources":{"PrecisionTraderBot.js":{"name":"PrecisionTraderBot.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Josh"},{"caption":"Moving Average Delta","authorId":140606,"indicators":["Moving Average Delta"],"id":"fe63b801-fd68-41f4-a4a1-09969e030178","text":"This study tracks two moving average (Simple, Exponential, Hull, Weighted, and Modified) and plots their delta in a histogram.","likes":0