ngs automatically displays the swing chart and trend on any timeframe you choose. There is an  option to set the swing points as arrows and/or ZigZag lines","updated":"2025-11-06T19:59:05.681Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"aad7de05-e018-44fd-a072-0d2022e1f09c","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["Gann Swings"],"authorId":5773555,"likes":0,"trendingScore":28,"usageScore":410,"shares":636,"sources":{"GannSwingLines.js":{"name":"GannSwingLines.js"}},"images":[],"author":"OverTrader"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Sethmo CCI + EMA","authorId":130646,"indicators":["Sethmo CCI + EMA"],"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Sethmo CCI + EMA","id":"69df5ca8-fd5c-43b3-a485-6b4140a4a6d5","updated":"2021-04-18T21:44:18.032Z","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"shares":633,"trendingScore":1,"usageScore":25,"sources":{"sethmotikiCciEMA.js":{"name":"sethmotikiCciEMA.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Seth Mo"},{"caption":"MACDX - Wave Indicator with HTF","text":"This is calculated similar to the WaveTrend Oscillator with very specific settings shown as a histogram.  It also has a higher time frame line with the same calculations overlaid using more bars. Together, they produce a reliable way to fade pullbacks, find turning points in price, and keep you on the right side of the market.  Combined with the concept of market structure it is valuable for sclaping and swing trading alike.  You can trade the extremes of the waves following price structure, or use the line slope as your trend direction if you struggle reading price.  If you take the time to read the patterns in the MACDX and it's relashionship to price, it is powerful.  Pay attention to the waves or the line crossing over the zero line, as well as the wave and line extremes.  The HTF (line) is rougly 4.2 times higher than the current timeframe (histogram), no matter what type of chart you are viewing.  I wouldn't suggest modifying the variables. Uncheck the 2 smoothing lines in settings  - Dave True","updated":"2025-05-25T17:56:48.833Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"cf6cc721-c02e-4ab4-9e0d-ebc4b5e5735c","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["MACDX"],"authorId":2221374,"likes":0,"shares":631,"trendingScore":16,"usageScore":53,"sources":{"waveTrendDual.js":{"name":"waveTrendDual.js"}},"images":["a2b6157a-73e8-47d6-9955-7708f5e54bd5","cb1c3d45-1285-4614-897b-e3824a0a06da"],"author":"Dave True"},{"caption":"Bid Ask VPOC","text":"This indicator identifies the highest buy and sell volume levels within each bar, highlighting the dominant price points based on bid and ask volumes. It dynamically calculates and plots a box around the highest buy or sell volume level in real time for each bar.","updated":"2025-05-19T12:37:43.523Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"25023d0d-1c2c-4d12-ad73-88fedce12c91","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["Bid/Ask VPOC"],"authorId":4753272,"likes":0,"shares":625,"trendingScore":14,"usageScore":90,"sources":{"bidAskVPOC.js":{"name":"bidAskVPOC.js"}},"images":[],"author":" Bid Ask VPOC"},{"caption":"Elliot Wave Oscillator","text":"Elliot Wave Oscillator using EMA 5 and 35 to predict trend","updated":"2025-02-17T16:45:38.641Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"a05a776b-3831-46bc-adf1-d4de29c1823b","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["My Elliot Wave Oscillator"],"authorId":4293389,"likes":0,"trendingScore":14,"shares":625,"usageScore":237,"sources":{"myEWO.js":{"name":"myEWO.js"}},"images":[],"author":" Joe Vandal"},{"caption":"USTMACD","authorId":89218,"indicators":["MACD & BB's"],"text":"Macd & BBs","id":"5d6828d6c55c6e6bbfa14f37","updated":"2019-08-29T19:34:46.891Z","likes":0,"shares":625,"trendingScore":1,"usageScore":25,"sources":{"USTMacdBBs":{"name":"USTMacdBBs.js"}},"ima