 (stop hunts) on the chart.\n\n A Liquidity Sweep occurs when price briefly wicks beyond a prior swing high or low (taking out resting stop orders), then immediately closes back inside - signalling that smart money has consumed liquidity and is likely to reverse.\n \nDetection criteria (matches the analysis engine):\n *  1. Find the swing high/low over the last N bars (lookback)\n *  2. Current bar wicks beyond that level by at least `swingBreachTicks`\n *  3. Current bar CLOSES back on the inside of the level (wick, not a full break)\n *  4. The wick extension is less than `maxWickTicks` (filters genuine breakouts)\n *  5. Within `reversalLookforward` bars, price moves at least `minReversalTicks` away from the wick extreme (confirms the reversal)\n \n Visual:\n- Vertical spike line from swept level → wick extreme\n- Horizontal cap line at the wick extreme\n- Dashed extension line at the swept level, projected forward","updated":"2026-03-06T02:33:33.893Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"3d4f56ce-79c8-4c00-b39d-a2a116d99951","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["Liquidity Sweeps"],"authorId":155358,"likes":0,"shares":540,"trendingScore":56,"usageScore":195,"sources":{"liquiditySweep.js":{"name":"liquiditySweep.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Vamp"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"template","module":"funCharts","caption":"FiskySwift Scalping","indicators":[],"authorId":792594,"usageScore":0,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Used indicators: Simple Moving Average, LDT - Remaining Time and Ticks, LDT - Magnum's 3/6/9/12 Levels, High Volume Area, Sethmo Large Delta Bubbles, Sethmo Price Axis Volume Delta, Moving Average - w/Trend Color, Tiki ADX","id":"b07c527b-d397-4ae4-9428-0f01680a8586","updated":"2023-11-03T12:26:10.762Z","likes":0,"shares":539,"trendingScore":5,"sources":{"FiskySwift Scalping":{"name":"FiskySwift Scalping.template.tradovate"}},"images":[],"author":"FiskySwift Scalp"},{"caption":"Order Block","text":"An Order Block is the last opposing candle before a significant displacement move.\n\n- Bullish OB: last bearish candle before a strong rally → acts as support on retest\n- Bearish OB: last bullish candle before a strong selloff → acts as resistance on retest\n\nFeatures:\n- Detects OBs using configurable displacement threshold (in ticks)\n- Extends boxes forward until \"mitigated\" (price enters the zone)\n- Dashed midpoint line inside each box (key entry/reaction level)\n- Toggle to show/hide mitigated OBs (keeps the chart clean)\n- Toggle between body-only or full-wick OB zone\n- Configurable colors, opacity, and max displayed OBs","updated":"2026-03-06T00:20:11.310Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"5c93f763-96d3-4b64-96a0-02ddd943f940","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["ICT Order Blocks"],"authorId":155358,"likes":0,"shares":539,"trendingScore":60,"usageScore":231,"sources":{"orderBlock.js":{"name":"orderBlock.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Vamp"},{"caption":"OpeningRangeBreakout","text":"Opening Range Breakout (ORB) with Dynamic Scaling\nOverview\n\nThis indicator calculates and plots the Opening Range (OR) based on a user-defined time window. It is designed to identify the initial balance of the market, providing key support and resistance levels (High, Low, and Midpoint) that often dictate the intraday trend.\nTechnical Features\n\n    Time-Defined Range: Users can specify the exact start and end time (Hour/Minute) to define the opening range (e.g., the first 30 minutes of the RTH session).\n\n    Intraday Reset Logic: The algorithm automatically detects session transitions and resets the High/Low values daily to ensure accurate calculations for every new trading day.\n\n    Dynamic Real-Time Calculation: Unlike \"static\" indicators that only plot after the range is closed, this version updates the High and Low levels tick-by-tick during the formation period. This allows traders to monitor \"price discovery\" and volatility expansion in real-time.\n\n    Midpoint (Mean) Level: Automatically calculates the","updated":"2026-03-31T17:53:40.268Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"ebba07d1-1963-4498-9252-270272d99cf6","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["Opening Range Breakout"],"authorId":7146966,"likes":0,"trendingScore":98,"usageScore":877,"shares":538,"sources":{"orBreakout.js":{"name":"orBreakout.js"}},"images":[],"author":" Massimo"},{"caption":"Macdbbbsss DTA","authorId":83809,"indicators":["MACD BBs"],"text":"MACDBBSSS","id":"8d0d5ada-07c0-4cf8-b351-ddfdcc1da727","updated":"2020-06-29T00:33:48.920Z","likes":0,"shares":537,"trendingScore":3,"usageScore":41,"sources":{"Macdbbss":{"name":"Macdbbss.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Nicolas Bastidas"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"DeltaTrend_V3","indicators":["Delta Trend V3"],"authorId":140399,"allowDirectLink":true,"id":"5ce114a0-0ade-4bb7-9d9c-0c53d6790b2b","text":"delta trend v3 no filter to be used with delta target","updated":"2021-04-22T14:22:36.697Z","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"usageScore":2,"shares":536,"trendingScore":3,"sources":{"DeltaTrend_V3.js":{"name":"DeltaTrend_V3.js"}},"images":[],"author":"DragonPT"},{"caption":"NCK Footprint Divergence Absorption Labels and Edge Exhaustion","text":"Credits / Lineage:\n     This script is modified by NorCalKyle via ChatGPT prompts, which was\n     modified by MarketXero for the Investitrade community, from the\n     'Hector - Footprint' indicator (originally derived from Sethmo).\n\n   What it does:\n     * Renders per-bar footprint profiles (price-by-volume at each tick).\n     * Plots Bid/Ask Delta bars and Total Volume bars per price level.\n     * Highlights zero-prints (true blanks on one side of the book).\n     * Shows divergence **text only** (no dots/icons) when:\n    * Zero-prints are always colored pink; when “Zero-prints only” is ON