:"5bbf2a72c2fb88ecd6917000","text":"Wanted to have BBand with 1 stdev bands vice 2","updated":"2018-10-11T11:01:37.071Z","likes":0,"shares":509,"trendingScore":2,"usageScore":2,"sources":{"BBand_StDev_RD":{"name":"BBand_StDev_RD.js"}},"images":[],"author":"Rathrbsrfng"},{"hidden":false,"entityType":"chartIndicator","link":"","caption":"Price Change / Delta","entitlement":false,"indicators":["Price Delta Elasticity All"],"authorId":1331617,"allowDirectLink":true,"text":"Elasticity Measure of Delta. Measure how big was the response in price to delta. \nBar is red for Negative Delta, and Green for Positive Delta.\n\nWhat is this inficator good for:\n1- High negative values: divergence alert. Predicts a run opposite of the color of the candle (large negative green candle is a bearish signal). \nI have seen this signal work quite well. Look for 1 very high negative number or 2  close to each other.\n2- High Positive values: Price overacting. Can indicate the beggining of a run, but it is normally seen at the end of a run. This is a weak/low probability signal.\n3- Compare candles:  I created this indicator with the idea of showing which side of the market gets better sensitivity during an absortion/consolidation period. I was expecting to see an increase in sensitivity/elasticity towards the next move. I have not yet seem this signal working.","id":"e9166102-28a9-4ccf-b4c8-ddd341a36a07","updated":"2023-07-02T18:38:54.656Z","obfuscated":false,"likes":0,"trendingScore":5,"usageScore":7,"shares":509,"sources":{"PriceDeltaElasticityAll.js":{"name":"PriceDeltaElasticityAll.js"}},"images":["cabd5299-8fbe-462a-9609-2023f6ddb857"],"author":"HoracioO"},{"caption":"SpotGamma Daily Levels","text":"used Grok to code this based off of SpotGamma's ToS study.","updated":"2025-02-16T03:57:04.310Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"e23a8edb-88da-4ee4-954e-81c2b8ee5018","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["Spot Gamma Level