Used indicators: SMA, WMA, EMA, ATR TrailStop w/Fib Targets, TMA, LBR_ThreeTenOscillator, Tiki Ergodic Oscillator, MACD BBs, TMO (True Momentum Oscillator), Wave Trend Oscillator, Tiki Elder Impulse, Range Forecast, Bulls vs Bears, Tiki Awesome Oscillator, HMA","updated":"2025-07-03T14:15:17.653Z","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"entityType":"template","module":"funCharts","indicators":[],"id":"63939a29-2f98-4a31-8904-21c9751e9ae0","authorId":4659674,"likes":0,"usageScore":0,"shares":82,"trendingScore":0,"sources":{"CE 2 Min":{"name":"CE 2 Min.template.tradovate"}},"images":[],"author":"CLB"},{"indicators":[],"caption":"High R:R % Win Rate","text":"Used indicators: Tiki Opening Range, EMA, LDT - Stochastic RSI, Donkey Face RSI, CE VWAP\nLong Entries when Stoch RSI crossing down from overbought and RSI Histo is decreasing or crossing 48 EMA.\nShort Entries when Stoch RSI crossing up from oversold and RSI Histo increasing or crossing 48 EMA.\n8 and 14 EMA pair for trend and reversal confluence. \nVWAP for wick tests and trend confluence. \nOpening Range Breakout set from true NY open 8am est for a 1hr Opening range to 9am est. Entries when Stoch RSI and RSI Histo agree with the move. And you are able to take trades inside of the opening range before NY open Stoch RSI and RSI Histo will tell you when. \nVery high win rate strategy. \nYou can scroll for months and there are a handful of days where you either would not take a trade due to chop based on a breakout or just chop in the opening range in general. \nThe usual 9:30-9:45 ORB strategy creates too large of a range in a lot of cases, so entries are either late or faked out.","updated":"2025-03-14T21:58:17.073Z","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"entityType":"template","module":"funCharts","id":"101799ae-35a9-4d0d-8480-4ac446f34db2","authorId":3974228,"likes":0,"usageScore":0,"shares":82,"trendingScore":2,"sources":{"High R:R % Win Rate":{"name":"High R:R % Win Rate.template.tradovate"}},"images":[],"autho