\nA traditional supertrend uses fixed settings — say ATR 10, multiplier 3.0 — regardless of whether you're on a 1-minute or a daily chart. Ours automatically adjusts both values based on the timeframe you're actually on. The 1–5 minute chart gets tighter, faster settings. The 4-hour and daily get wider, smoother settings. So it behaves appropriately at every timeframe without you touching a dial.\n2. HTF trend filter\nBefore a Buy or Sell label prints, ours checks a higher timeframe EMA — automatically selected based on your chart timeframe (e.g. if you're on 5min it checks the 15min EMA, if you're on 1hr it checks the 4hr). The raw trend line always flips instantly, but the label only fires when the higher timeframe agrees. This stops you from fighting the larger trend.\n3. Volume confirmation\nThe flip bar must show elevated volume — above the 20-bar average by a user-defined threshold. A supertrend flip on thin volume is often a fake-out. This gate filters t","updated":"2026-03-24T20:23:42.243Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"33b4d557-bd67-4dad-b9bd-f4f6514a38c3","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["Smooths Trend Breaker"],"authorId":6886127,"likes":0,"shares":29,"trendingScore":3,"usageScore":1,"sources":{"SmoothsTrendBreaker.js":{"name":"SmoothsTrendBreaker.js"}},"images":[],"author":"CaptainSmooth"},{"caption":"TYJHeiken4","text":"trend","updated":"2025-04-20T16:48:04.057Z","link":"","allowDirectLink":true,"hidden":false,"id":"606e75df-5da2-4dc4-948a-82edc872a7d1","entityType":"chartIndicator","obfuscated":false,"entitlement":false,"indicators":["Fast EMA-style Heikin Ashi with color memory"],"authorId":2605598,"likes":0,"shares":29,"usageScore":0,"trendingScore":0,"sources":{"TYJHeiken4.js":{"name":"TYJHeiken4.js"}},"images":[],"author":"swolio"},{"caption":"Trend of the Bollinger Bands Width","text":"Trend of the Bollinger Bands Width for use in other indicators or alone","updated":"2025-0